text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason

text:
we all have challenges that we must face, it doesn't matter how many times you run they are still going to be there, and will keep knocking until you say "right today i am going to stop running and deal with whatever comes my way" some challenges are harder than others, they will come with lessons and gifts. today i am grateful for amazing friends, strength to face what i need to, and the knowledge that although there is that little voice of fear, there is always hope.
❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🕉️🦄🙏🌈🧘‍♀️🤺🌻

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason

text:
vor zwei tagen hab ich geträumt, ich sei spiderman und sah es als zeichen, den film zu netflixen. man muss nicht simone de beauvoir gelesen haben, damit einem die dümmlichen rollenklischees ins auge springen:
der held? 👉 ein mann.
der bösewicht? 👉 ein mann.
der smarte, junge unternehmer? 👉 ein mann.
der zeitungsverleger? 👉 ein mann.
der bankfuzzi? 👉 ein mann.
frauen kommen übrigens auch vor. sie werden von den männern gerettet. die arme, alte oma. das kleine mädchen aus dem feuer. die junge, hübsche nachbarin m.j. sogar gleich mehrmals - und immer im flatternden und später zerfetztem kleidchen 🙄. (mal davon abgesehen, dass sie auf ihre unerwiderte liebe zu peter nicht damit darauf reagiert, einfach ihr ding zu machen, sondern einen anderen typen heiraten will). #rollenklischees #film #filmabend #spiderman #girlsgetequal #gleichberechtigung #girlscandoanything #sexistischekackscheisse #feminismus #metoo

text:
instagram выпустил обзор тенденций платформы за 2018 год: чем жило сообщество социальной сети в уходящем году2⃣0⃣1⃣8⃣
самым популярным стикером в stories стал heart love от arata, а самым часто используемым фильтром для лица - heart eyes😍 в ленте эмодзи «сердце»❤ встречалось в комментариях более 14 миллиардов раз😱
что касается интересов аудитории, то в этом году продолжали расти в популярности фото и видео, которые вызывают приятные до мурашек ощущения (asmr): например, резка мыла.
в игре fortnite также наблюдается взрывной рост: #fortnite - очень быстро набирающий популярность хэштег. крупнейший конкурс вирусного танца года также проходил в instagram - это #inmyfeelingschallenge.
миллионы людей использовали instagram для того, чтобы их голоса были услышаны. основными пропагандистскими хэштегами года были #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k). это демонстрирует, что instagram можно использовать для того, чтобы высказать свою точку зрения на важные вещи👍🏼
а что заметили вы?🧐
📲справки по телефону: 0555 235-598

a #hartwell man was arrested this week for allegedly raping a 5-year-old girl.
.
irun robinson, 21, was arrested on tuesday after investigations by the police connected him to a rape case of a minor on nov. 14.
.
#robinson, who is the prime #suspect in the case, is said to have had prior offences. he was sentenced to 22months for breaking and entering in 2015 when he was just 18 and later transferred to volunteers for #america to complete is sentence but escaped the facility in #2016
.
robinson was recaptured and pleaded guilty to escape in #march of this year, getting another sentence of nine months in #prison.
.
robinson is now being held on a $100,000 bond at the #hamilton county #justice center awaiting trial for the #rape of the 5-year-old victim.
.
.

text:
“16” 1 out of 2 pieces i did for the amazing “dark and light” show for @heygrrlcollective. 
my “dark” was focused on healing from trauma from wwasp. being trapped at spring creek, i felt like an alien who was crucified for her beliefs that went against the abusive and illegal ethos of synanon cult society. here, if any of us were outspoken about our independent thoughts, especially confronting or standing up to abuse, we were seen as threats, defiant, unruly, damaged and therefore punished and crucified for it. this piece was a “fuck you” piece to them really.

text:
📚『８２年生まれ、キム・ジヨン』

大ベストセラー小説『82年生まれ、キム・ジヨン』を昨日読みました。読み進めていくうちに、ノンフィクション😃を読んでいるような、不思議な感覚になってきて。キム・ジヨンは存在しているような感覚になります✨そして、今いる場所で、多文化や差別のない平等の権利を考える一冊に📕なると思います。
 k-popアイドルユニットのred velvet・アイリーンが「読んだ」と発言しただけで大炎上し、少女時代・スヨンは「読んだ後、何でもないと思っていたことが、思い浮かんだ。女性という理由で受けてきた不平等なことが思い出され、急襲を受けた気分だった」(『90年生まれチェ・スヨン』 より)と、bts・rmは「示唆するところが格別で、印象深かった」(naver vライブ生放送 より)と言及されています。
さらに韓国で社会現象にまで発展した一冊です。台湾でもベストセラーとなり、ベトナム、英国、イタリア、フランス、スペインなど16ゕ国で翻訳決定。また 俳優コン・ユさんとチョン・ユミさんが映画「82年生まれキム・ジヨン」に出演されます。

tweet_full:
📚『８２年生まれ、キム・ジヨン』

大ベストセラー小説『82年生まれ、キム・ジヨン』を昨日読みました。読み進めていくうちに、ノンフィクション😃を読んでいるような、不思議な感覚になってきて。キム・ジヨンは存在しているような感覚になります✨そして、今いる場所で、多文化や差別のない平等の権利を考える一冊に📕なると思います。
 k-popアイドルユニットのred velvet・アイリーンが「読んだ」と発言しただけで大炎上し、少女時代・スヨンは「読んだ後、何でもないと思っていたことが、思い浮かんだ。女性という理由で受けてきた不平等なことが思い出され、急襲を受けた気分だった」(『90年生まれチェ・スヨン』 より)と、bts・rmは「示唆するところが格別で、印象深かった」(naver vライブ生放送 より)と言及されています。
さらに韓国で社会現象にまで発展した一冊です。台湾でもベストセラーとなり、ベトナム、英国、イタリア、フランス、スペインなど16ゕ国で翻訳決定。また 俳優コン・ユさんとチョン・ユミさんが映画「82年生まれキム・ジヨン」に出演されます。

text:
меган фокс рассказала, почему не поддерживает #metoo. 
в недавнем интервью изданию the new york times меган фокс рассказала, что не поддерживает современных голливудских феминисток и движение #metoo. актриса призналась, что неоднократно подвергалась харрасменту, однако сомневается в том, что справедливость восторжествует когда-либо. 
она также напомнила, что ещё несколько лет назад пыталась поднять эту тему, вступив в противостояние с влиятельным мужчиной. однако феминистки её не поддержали. фокс не стала подробно рассказывать о том случае, отметив, что ей многократно приходилось сталкиваться с повышенным вниманием со стороны мужчин. 
стоит отметить, что несколько лет назад фокс действительно обвинила режиссёра майкла бэя в намеренной сексуализации своего образа в картине «трансформеры». тогда все от неё отмахнулись, заявив, что она наговаривает на постановщика.

#meganfox #меганфокс #empirestatebuilding #wtc #newyorkcity #centralpark #midtown #downtown #timessquare

text:
сервис instagram назвал самое счастливое место в мире
15 декабря 2018
самым счастливым местом в мире по мнению пользователей instagram является токийский диснейленд reuters
соцсеть instagram обнародовала итоги работы сервиса в 2018 году. в официальном блоге соцсети были опубликованы результаты исследования активности ее пользователей.
самым счастливым местом в мире по мнению пользователей instagram является токийский диснейленд - под фотографиями, сделанными в этом парке развлечений, было поставлено больше всего радостных смайлов.
самым популярным фильтром для историй среди пользователей instagram стали сердечки, накладываемые на глаза, а самым часто используемым стикером - двигающийся "лайк" в виде сердца. пользователи соцсети также оставили 14 млрд смайликов с сердчеками в комментариях к записям в аккаунтах.
в тройку наиболее популярных хэштегов вошли #metoo (примерно полтора миллиона упоминаний), #timesup (597 тысяч) и #marchforourlives (562 тысячи).
#сервис  #счастливоеместо #диснейленд #парк #сердечки #лайки #смайлики

text: i’m sorry to do this on here, i’m afraid i’ll lose followers because of this. just released thursday from an unexpected hospitalization and god i  am hurting so badly i cannot bear it. my mother has disowned me. kicked out of my home. friends are sick of me. i have nothing. my health is on the trash. my bills are higher than my christmas tree. my ex who tried to kill me and beat me regularly is being released from prison in february instead of 3 years from now like the da promised me. feel like my world is crashing. here is something from an assignment from group therapy the other day. i hate myself because it isn’t perfect and i’m a writer and it’s such shit but it’s honest and it’s where i’m at right now. the police took my medical marijuana, my medical marijuana card is missing along with $200 of medical marijuana products and i am in so much pain and distress. i have no income to just throw money around and am not working right now i am now beside myself because how could the police have taken my medical card?  they deny it. i will make a longer post explaining later i am in such a horrible state right now i cannot breathe. thank you to anyone reading this and please any prayers good vibes anything i am in such anguish physically and mentally i don’t know where to go or what to do and my heart just hurts so much i feel like it is going to give out i need a lawyer i need help but i can’t do research i have a concussion my fourth of the year i am so overwhelmed i will post more later i  so sorry for oversharing i just don’t know where else to go and i have literally no other outlet  #recovery #ptsd #medicalmarijuanapatient #inpatientrecovery #eatingdisorderrecovery #prisonerofmymind #depression #anxiety #heartbroken #policebrutality #survivor #ptsdrecovery #metoo #ibelieveher #woar #mentalhealthawareness #relapse #domesticviolence #domesticviolencesurvivor

text:
idag är det en sorgens dag😥

tarzan som delat hem mellan mej och min syster ska få somna in.
en undebar trogen spridare av lugn, trygghet, värme och glädje. 
vi har haft många fina stunder ihop och han var en trogen soldat när vi hade vår kampanj att skapa trygghet genom "jakt på våldtäktsmän". nattvandring i syfte att ge kvinnor trygghet i natten. 
samt ge vissa "män" en fingervisning om sitt beteende i natten.

men efter en försämring i hans hälsa och smärta så har i samråd med veterinär beslutats om avslut. 
sorg och saknad... vila i frid tarzan❤

#restinpeace #hund #dog #pitbull #canecorso #animal #doglover #metoo #manlighet #macho #heforshe
name: 🇸🇪Kalle Aka Bonecrusher

text:
i love men. always will, always have.

because of my rather difficult relationship with women sometimes i gravitated easily towards friendships with men. i love their precisiveness, the focus they have (without getting lost in the details like i love doing) and their amazing advice. 
this year seemed to have been the general men bashing year. my feeds were all about surpression of women by men and the #metoo movement that highlighted a very important fact of what women have to deal with but it also made all men look like they are egotistical, narcassistic a**holes.

now, i am not here to tell you that you can't have that opinion but i refuse to jump on that train of negativity.

yes, i have had my fair share of heart breaks and sexual harrassment. but i also had horrible experiences where women betrayed my trust and hurt me deeply. i turned things around and instead of feeling like a victim i asked myself: how can i learn from the situation and avoid these situations in the future? 
we will always have duality in life and there will always be good people and people who we consider 'bad' for not playing according to our rules and that won't change!

but together we are stronger.
together we can compliment each other with our own, unique strengths.

and thankfully i have lot of men in my life who are kind-hearted, supportive and willing to learn.

this current era is not easy for men nor women. we are all re-defining who we are. i, for my part, want to live in peace with the opposite sex and don't need fighting, finger-pointing (on the past) and wanting to be right at any cost. my life is too short and instead of concentrating on this i rather help my clients become the best version of themselves and live a balanced, happy life ❤️
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#confidencecoachingforwomen #balance #men #oppositesattract #wecomplimenteachother #duality #beuniquelyyou

text:
📝15 декабря – купить наряд на корпоративное мероприятие/новогоднюю ночь.

тренды зимы 2019: ⠀
⠀
🐘 анималистический принт 
этой осенью никуда не скрыться от обилия анималистических принтов. живописные пятна шкур леопарда, оцелота, зебры и тигра густо покрыли подиумы четырех главных модных столиц мира. особенно эффектно выглядят нетрадиционные цветовые сочетания "хищных" окрасов с розовым, малиновым или алым. ⠀
⠀
🥋 многослойность
многослойность нельзя назвать чистым трендом осени-зимы 2018/2019. как только наступают холода, самым естественным образом наряды начинают сползаться в один большой текстильный "пирог". главное отличие этого сезона - самые "вкусные" сочетания фактур. нейлон с мехом или шерстью, бархат и кожа. ⠀
⠀
💃 платья из кожи
кожаные наряды в эпоху #metoo выглядят настоящими модными латами. на поясе или нет, длинные или минимально короткие, мрачновато черные или жизнерадостно оранжевые - без них модный пазл этой зимы не сложится. ⠀
⠀
❄ серебро
наряды в монолуках под кодовым названием all in silver сделают их обладательницу похожей на стремительную серебряную пулю, на девушку из футуристических 1960-х или на главную диву танцпола из восьмидесятых. ⠀
⠀
🎀 твид
без твида не обходится ни один осенне-зимний сезон. и если раньше по какой-то причине вы обходили этот благородный материал стороной, то новый сезон - самое время научиться носить сложносочиненные наряды из твида. ⠀
⠀
📍 топ-10 оттенков 2019 года:
quetzal green (зеленый квезаль); ⠀
red pear (красная груша); ⠀
valiant poppy (героический мак); ⠀
russet orange (рыжий апельсин); ⠀
crocus petal (лепесток крокуса); ⠀
nebulas blue (туманно-синий); ⠀
ceylon yellow (цейлонский желтый); ⠀
limelight (лаймлайт); ⠀
martini olive (оливковый); ⠀
ultra violet (ультрафиолет). ⠀
⠀
гильдия hr-клубов желает вам отличного праздника! веселитесь и будьте в тренде, тогда год золотой свиньи 🐗 обязательно будет к вам благосклонен! 😉 
какой выберете цвет для своего новогоднего наряда? 👇🏻 #hr #hrclub #гильдияhrклубов #управлениеперсоналом #тренды2019 #цвета2019

text:
nama scott gelb menjadi sorotan utama dalam permasalahan ini, karena ketika investigasi dan wawancara mendalam yang dilakukan oleh kotaku,  8 bulan sebelum artikel tentang kasus ini terbit agustus tahun ini, namanya paling sering muncul. ia dituding acap kali melakukan pelecehan seksual sepertinya secara tidak sopan dengan menyentuh karyawan laki-laki atau perempuan hingga kentut didekat wajah mereka.⠀
.⠀
menyewa lembaga hukum seyfarth shaw untuk melakukan investigasi, akhirnya riot games menetapkan hukuman kepada coo mereka. melalui email yang dikirimkan kepada seluruh karyawan minggu ini, riot ceo nicolo laurent mengindikasikan bahwa banyak investigasi internal yang tidak bisa dipublikasikan kepada publik, namun mengingat posisi gelb di perusahaan, board of director ingin hukuman kepada gelb dipublikasi dengan jelas.⠀
.⠀
dalam email tersebut juga, laurent mengatakan banyak tuduhan kepada gelb tidaklah benar. namun tidak dijelaskan investigasi mana atau tuduhan apa yang tidak benar kepada  gelb. hukuman yang didapat oleh gelb tidaklah berat, apalagi di era #metoo sekarang ini, dimana tidak sedikit petinggi perusahaan yang harus kehilangan jabatannya akibat perilaku seksual yang dilakukannya di tempat kerja.⠀
⠀

website : esports.id⠀
fanpage : @esportsindo⠀
youtube : esports id⠀
⠀

text:
gerty theresa cori (august 15, 1896 – october 26, 1957) was a jewish austrian-american biochemist who became the third woman—and first american woman—to win a nobel prize in science, and the first woman to be awarded the nobel prize in physiology or medicine, in 1947, for her role in the discovery of glycogen metabolism.
gerty was not a nickname, but rather she was named after an austrian warship.
growing up at a time when women were marginalized in science and allowed few educational opportunities, she gained admittance to medical school, where she met her future husband carl ferdinand cori; upon their graduation in 1920, they married.
because of deteriorating conditions in europe, the couple emigrated to the united states in 1922.
gerty cori continued her early interest in medical research, collaborating in the laboratory with carl.
she published research findings coauthored with her husband, as well as publishing singly.
unlike her husband, she had difficulty securing research positions, and the ones she obtained provided meager pay.
her husband insisted on continuing their collaboration, though he was discouraged from doing so by the institutions that employed him.
with her husband carl and argentine physiologist bernardo houssay, gerty cori received the nobel prize in 1947 for the discovery of the mechanism by which glycogen—a derivative of glucose—is broken down in muscle tissue into lactic acid and then resynthesized in the body and stored as a source of energy (known as the cori cycle).
they also identified the important catalyzing compound, the cori ester.
in 2004, both gerty and carl cori were designated a national historic chemical landmark in recognition of their work in clarifying carbohydrate metabolism.
in 1957, gerty cori died after a ten-year struggle with myelosclerosis.
she remained active in the research laboratory until the end.
cori was honored by the release of a us postal service stamp in april, 2008.
the us department of energy named the nersc-8 supercomputer installed in 2015/2016 after cori.

and last but not least.... "i saw mommy kissing santa claus" = promotes adultery

if this offends anyone, please don’t bother to tell me as i just don’t care. i drink coffee stronger coffee stronger than your feelings. 😂👍🏼😘

text:
no solo le pasa a las mujeres, jamás lo conte, solo a unas amigas que la verdad en el momento lo tomamos como un chiste pero no! ahora viendolo bien, quizas la mayoria se burle, pero está en cada uno...
creo que me ánimo y es el momento mno puedo guardarmelo, porque la verdad ser niño y pasar por eso, es aberrante...
esto me pasó cuando tenia 7 años, 7 años loco solo 7, ir a la casa de mi abuela, jugar y divertirse con los primos (cosas que hacemos a esa edad), era hora de almorzar y todos bajaron a la mesa, yo me quede un ratito más viendo tele en la habitación de mi abuela, y en eso aparece un "primo" (en ese entonces tenia unos 21 o 23 años), se paro en la puerta y saco su pene ya erecto, me dijo "tocalo", yo la verdad me quede como tonto, me dijo otra vez "tocalo" y en eso le dije no, me miraba y practicamente se masturbaba, seguia insistiendo y le dije "no, si sube alguien? y me pegan?", yo re inocente pense que era a mi a quien iban a golpear, en eso me dice "no va a subir nadie veni", yo la verdad no sabia que hacer, tenia mucho miedo a que me peguen, quería que lo toque y cuantas cosas más pasaron en su cabeza, depues de casi 12 años recien estoy cayendo en la realidad, de que yo no deberia de haber tenido miedo, si no él! tengo una impotencia de la puta madre!! y no puedo no imaginar lo que paso en su pequeño cerebro, la verdad fue algo muy muy feo eso, ser un niño y no saber como reaccionar, la verdad aún ahora no sé como decirlo, quizás ya lo supere o no, lo pienso y la verdad todos todos tenemos que estar unidos al 100%... #nosololespasaalasmujeres #bastadeacoso #infantil #metoo

text:
@semspeshawar held an event to encourage women entrepreneurs in kp last week. i was at the event as a panelist to discuss the challenges and opportunities for women in #kpk in the next five years. it was a good effort by sems but something bothered me big time.
a young school girl had a question about harassment and she was told by one of the panelist that if you stay within the limits of 'haya' and 'islam' you won't be harassed. by then i had stepped off the discussion forum and wasn't in a position to question it. but that was wrong on so many levels. it's a prime example of how our society blames the victim. i wanted to ask the respected lady to wear a burqa and then go travel on public transport and see how her pardah saves her from harassment.

i personally feel,  dressing up provocatively may invite extra harassment but dressing modestly doesn't actually save you from what is already out there. 
views?

#harrassment #victimblaming #sexualharrasment #women #eomenempowerment #girlboss #girlbosses #metoo

repost from @bloombergbusiness. at proventus group, we are proud to have pur senior management team be 100% women. wall street has adopted a new strategy in the #metoo era: avoid women altogether.

call it the pence effect, after u.s. vice president mike pence, who says he avoids dining alone with any women who aren't his wife.

in finance, the impact could essentially be gender segregation, and wall street risks becoming even more of a boy's club, rather than less of one. “women are grasping for ideas on how to deal with it, because it is affecting our careers,” a senior vice president at wells fargo & co said. “it’s a real loss.”

text:
it’s a wonderful life was on last night - i love that movie!  when you stop and really think about it, this is a wonderful life.

sure, we can always find the negatives in our life; what we think is lacking in our life; what we wish we have and don’t. however, if we focus and appreciate what it is we do have, we find out how rich we really are - rich in love, support, and health.

let’s start our day appreciating what it is that we do have instead of wishing for what we don’t because, it is a wonderful life 💜

text:
что объеденяет диснейленд в токио и мистическую хакасию?

сотрудники instagram проанализировали поставленные пользователями социальной сети смайлики, геолокации и хештеги, опубликовав итоги 2018 года. об этом сообщается на официальном сайте instagram.

самой счастливой геолокацией на планете instagram признал диснейленд в токио. больше всего счастливых смайликов в 2018 году пользователи ставили именно под фотографиями из японского диснейленда.

самыми часто используемыми хештегами в 2018 году стали #metoo, #timesup и #marchforourlives. кроме этого, чаще всего пользователи использовали в качестве фильтра для лица изображение сердечек на глазах.

ранее аналитическое агентство турстат составило рейтинг лучших и популярных мест для мистического туризма в россии, половина которого пришлась на сибирские регионы — алтай, иркутскую область, бурятию и хакасию.

text:
12-wie of wat heb je in 2018 losgelaten?
ik liet los dat je een bedrijf runnen en reizen eigenlijk niet goed kunt combineren. dat kan dus wel. sommige plannen waar ik te lang aan vast hield liet ik los, zoals: ik moet een onlineprogramma aanbieden, nee, ik moet aanbieden wat ik leuk vind en ik ben nu eenmaal die coach die het liefst persoonlijk en op maat werkt. ik liet het idee los dat ik vooral lachende selfies moet maken voor social media liefst vol in de make-up en in een jurk en #lovemyjoblovemylife teksten moet hashtaggen ;) (nee, lieve mensen, ik heb nog steeds geen mooie beeldbank met glamourfoto’s, komt misschien nog wel ;) ik ben toch echt meer een wandelschoentype die soms in een jurk loopt.
.
de gedachte dat ik in gezelschap niet moet laten merken dat ik veel van voetballen weet (want ik heb daar gewoon verstand van :). de twijfel of ik me wel of niet zou uitspreken over #metoo. wel dus. mijn hoogtevrees kon ik behoorlijk loslaten; na jaren eindelijk aangepakt en actie ondernomen. dat ik me zou moeten aanpassen qua spirituele beleving en taal (want die beleef ik op mijn manier en in mijn eigen taal en die wijkt af van wat ik om me heen zie en lees en veel ervan zegt me ook helemaal niets.)
.
ik heb losgelaten (en eigenlijk nooit aangenomen) dat ik iets zou moeten veranderen omdat je, als je vijftig wordt, vanuit de buitenwereld ineens de boodschap krijgt dat er ‘iets’ moet veranderen in je leven, gezien de folders in de bus, ja, ze weten je ineens te vinden. wtf?! waarom?! ik vind mezelf helemaal niet oud en meestal jonger van geest dan sommige leeftijdsgenoten. zo. .
een assessment psycholoog zei ooit tegen me: u bent heel evenwichtig. daar baalde ik van want dat stond voor mij gelijk aan: boooring! saai! suf! nu, dát heb ik dus ook losgelaten. laat mij maar gewoon evenwichtig zijn en m’n eigen gang gaan zonder extreme uitschieters. :) en jij, wie of wat heb jij losgelaten? .
(foto: real madrid wint de champions league en daar genoot ik van! uren staan wachten tot de bus met spelers langs kwam maar het was het waard).

text:
lady her talk (lady's sparrow foundation, presented by lady's sparrow foundation, is breaking the silence around women's sexual health and building a community for women to heal, empower, and reclaim their bodies.come join us for a fireside chat with sexual health experts and learn more about our sexual health and the resources available while building your tribe of supportive women.

women's sexual health is complex and trusted resources are hard to find. learn more about everything from sexual pain to dysfunction, sex after pregnancy to sex after menopause, low libido to hyper libido, and sex and relationship. there will be a q&a to follow to ask those questions you've been too embarrassed to ask in an supportive and judgement free environment.

#silentnomore #powerofher #ladyssparrow #metoo #womenempowerment
#womenleaders #women
#womenssexuality
#sexualhealth #bravery
#breakingthestigma

text:
что нужно знать о бане?
в интернете куча разнообразной и противоречивой информации о пользе и вреде бани. для по-настоящему мудрого человека это всё белый шум. мудрец знает, что действительно важно знать о бане.

в бане живёт сварливый банный дух банник. он может запарить до смерти, подпереть дверь и даже насильно овладеть незадачливой девчулей. у банника есть гражданская жена обдериха, она ещё сварливей. у них с банником нет детей — немудрено, учитывая контрацептивные свойства высоких температур. поэтому обдериха не любит детей и особенно ненавидит беременных.

чтобы не столкнуться с возможными невзгодами, не стоит ходить в баню поодиночке, ночью и будучи больным или беременной. надеюсь, мои советы спасут не одну жизнь. благодарите в комментариях.

к чему это я: наш сегодняшний поход в баньку обломался, потому что пётр болеет. а я переживаю, что его болезнь спровоцирует гнев банника или обдерихи — мне не хочется быть изнасилованным семейной парой потусторонних смутьянов.

приходите лучше в бороду. ешьте, пейте, не бойтесь обдерихи.

p. s. картинка вышла по запросу «банька с чудовищами». думаю, именно так моя бывшая представляла себе нашу свадьбу.

#borodabar21 #borodabardaily #borodabarout #баня #мудрость #советы #обдериха #банник #metoo #этонеповодубить #сауна

text:
#nirbhayadiwas 🕯 #metoo
🔹
“cover your face with a ghoonghat!”
“adjust your hijab!”
“oh, your bra strap is showing!”
.
when are we going to stop telling her all such things, & rather start telling him to take away his haunting red eyes piercing through every pore of her body?
.
"because it all starts with one wrong look, one bad thought, & one evil intention!"
🔹
🌟 तेरी आँखें बलात्कारी 🌟 | #hasratwrites

जब भी सफर करती हूँ ट्रैन से,
तेरी घूरती आँखों को देख,
मुझको खौफ लगता है,
तेरी बेबाक बेशर्म आँखों में मुझको,
मेरी आबरू का बेहूदा मज़ाक दिखता है,
सुन ले तू आज एक बात ये मेरी,
ए छिछोरे, तेरी आँखें बलात्कारी!
.
जब सर से पाओं तक ढकी होती हूँ मैं,
भगवान को भी दिल में जाप रही होती हूँ मैं,
जब ताकती फिर भी मुझको आँखें ये तेरी,
लगता जैसे जिस्म में छुरी चुभा रहा कोई,
क्या जानेगा तू रंजिश ये मेरी,
ए छिछोरे, तेरी आँखें बलात्कारी!
.
क्या लगता तुझको तेरा तू जाने,
जब मर्दों के झुंड में अकेली फंस जाती हूँ,
लगता है खाने जैसी परोसी गयी हूँ थाली में मैं,
तेरी आँखों की टकमक काटों-चमचों की खनक लगती है मुझको,
क्यों ऐसे नीयत गद्दारी करती तेरी,
ए छिछोरे, तेरी आँखें बलात्कारी!
.
जो थोड़ी मुलायम सी है त्वचा ये मेरी,
तो कोई मलाई तो नहीं,
जो हलके से छूने को चाहते हो,
बता दूं तुझको कि कैसी आग है मुझमें,
जो एक नज़र मेरी तुझको खाक कर दे,
मेरी जुल्फें ये तेरा गला घोंट दे,
और मेरी उठी आवाज़ तुझको तबाह कर दे!
ए छिछोरे, अगर तेरी आँखें बलात्कारी,
तो मैं भी नारी, जो है सब पे भारी!
.
.
- हसरत [@hasratwrites]
.
.
.
.
.
#hasrat #nirbhaya #thehabitat #poetry #teriaankheinbalaatkari #kavita

this is why we have to ride for each other because no one else is...

#repost via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action 
4. contact gov bill haslam’s office and voice your thoughts 1st floor, state capitol nashville, tn 37243 (615) 741-2001 
5. his instagram @governorbillhaslam (remember, he is considering clemency so let’s honor and encourage that) 
6. watch the video: me facing life: cyntoia’s story - google it - it’s on @pbs and you can watch it online. ——————
update:  original art by <<<< @janaillustration >>>follow her! her work is perfection. 
i have tried so hard to find out who made the original piece that i used to stitch this. if you know, please let me know so that i can cite. ——— #blacklivesmatter #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #metoo #justice #freecyntoia #clemencyforcyntoia #resist 
#blm #cyntoiabrown

text:
“forgiveness and reconciliation are two different things, miri. forgiveness is a choice. it happens in an instant. reconciliation is a journey. it may take you the rest of your life. but forgiveness must come first.”
.
#read #104 of 2018: everything is wonderful by chelsea marcantel
.
at the age of twenty, miri was shunned by her amish family and community and forced to leave her homestead. in the wake of a familial tragedy, she returns to find that the ghosts of her past are still very much alive and that, for some, righteously held beliefs are thicker than blood.
.
a quiet yet steady drama for 3f, 3m. spoiler: another appropriate play in the #metoo era, though told from a perspective we don’t often see in new, 21st century plays.
.
would definitely recommend for high schools, community theatres, and colleges. there is a great dramatic monologue for miri and great scenework (especially for 1f, 1m) throughout.
.

tw: sexual assault. “i was assaulted by a guy that i thought i was friends with during my freshman year of college. he had a girlfriend at the time. i'd had a bad day and he stopped by my dorm room to say hi. when he was leaving, he hugged me, and then grabbed me and kissed me. i kept saying "no, stop, you have a girlfriend, no, what are you doing, no, stop, etc." but he kept kissing me and he forced his hands up my shirt and grabbed my breasts so hard i thought i'd have bruises. i kept saying "no" and "stop" and trying to push him away but he wouldn't stop. eventually he left. his girlfriend messaged me and it turns out that he told her that i came onto him. i tried to tell her what really happened but she wouldn't believe me and accused me of lying. then, the rumors started. this guy sexually assaulted me, ruined my reputation to cover himself, and all i could think was that it was my fault for allowing him into my dorm room.” - heather @spectacular_disaster

tw: sexual assault. “i was assaulted by a guy that i thought i was friends with during my freshman year of college. he had a girlfriend at the time. i'd had a bad day and he stopped by my dorm room to say hi. when he was leaving, he hugged me, and then grabbed me and kissed me. i kept saying "no, stop, you have a girlfriend, no, what are you doing, no, stop, etc." but he kept kissing me and he forced his hands up my shirt and grabbed my breasts so hard i thought i'd have bruises. i kept saying "no" and "stop" and trying to push him away but he would not stop. eventually he left. his girlfriend messaged me and it turns out that he told her that i came onto him. i tried to tell her what really happened but she would not believe me and accused me of lying. then, the rumors started. this guy sexually assaulted me, ruined my reputation to cover himself, and all i could think was that it was my fault for allowing him into my dorm room.” - heather @spectacular_disaster

.
.
since the age of 14, jayme’s life has been hell and she has one person to thank for it, pastor james madison.

he stood in the pulpit on sundays waving the same hands that abused her at night. he glorified god with the same mouth he used to chip away her self-esteem, daily. he was a man of god who had turned her away from the same god he told people they needed to serve.
:
he was the man who was supposed to pray for, take care of and eventually love her. instead he preyed on, took advantage of and shattered her heart before it had a chance to truly love someone else.
:
now, 14 years and a son later, she finds herself needing god yet she doesn’t know how to reach him. she longs for god but isn’t sure he can hear a sinner’s prayer until she starts to pray, dear god...

text:
so this is more of a #blogpost 
#triggerwarning .
.
.
i have talked about this several times but it is something that haunts me. i work as a #server and as a #transgender woman i have through the years learned one truth. men are #terrifying to be around them. to serve at a restaurant is to be objectified routinely. i am often #triggered as a #survivor i do know that certain things may make it even worse as even when people don’t know or mean to, it is still unnerving. however you look around and you see it happens a cross the board. my last table paying last night a man and his i’m assuming is girlfriend as he called her baby all night . they were finishing paying when he says “ i’ll leave a tip for your little ass too” and stairs me up and down. 😐 i’m now immediately turning into my feelings and into my mind over thinking 🤔. remembering that it happens to #metoo as a #transwoman it is two fold i have to either #embrace this overly feminine appearances work and then get #objectified , or just try and not pass and be #vilified . either way i’m in #danger and customers are so bad i am grabbed or get a creepy comment at least twice a month. and those are the way out of line comments and touches. i am routinely called pet names by strangers and touched nearly daily. 
it is amazing once you lose your #perceived #whitemale status and start to be seen as the #woman you are how often and grossly you are objectified and shamed just for being woman. it is a fucking disgusting problem only understood by those who have walked as a woman in a world of #patriarchal #chauvinism 
so keep your hands and comments to yourselves 🛑 ✋ thinking you can do what you want to #women and perceived women

sosial şəbəkə bu yolla ən çox xoşbəxt insanın olduğu geolokasiyanı müəyyən etməyə nail olub. "instagram”ın hesabatına görə, belə bir məkanın yaponiyada yerləşən "disneyland” atraksion və əyləncə aləminin olduğu məlum olub.

ekspertlər 2018-ci ilin ən populyar heşteqini müəyyən edə bilib. geri qoymaqda olduğumuz ildə istifadəçilər ən çox #metoo, #timesup və #marchforourlives heşteqlərindən istifadə edib.

text:
les réseaux sociaux vers de nouveaux idéaux ? 
à la question : « citez un nom célèbre représentant votre idéal féminin sur les réseaux sociaux ... » de notre questionnaire, nous avons eu des réponses telles que « emma watson ». en effet, emma watson peut être envisagée comme un idéal différent, qui ne répond pas aux critères d’hyper-sexualisation et qui est largement connu pour son implication pour la cause des femmes. elle participe au mouvement time's up, fondé en 2018 par plusieurs célébrités d'hollywood, luttant contre les dérives de harcèlement et violence sexuels en réponse à l'effet weinstein et au hashtag #metoo. elle est le visage de heforshe (« lui pour elle »), qui est une campagne de solidarité pour l'égalité des sexes lancée par l'onu femmes. changer le regard porté sur les femmes, via les femmes, certes, mais aussi via les hommes eux-mêmes, qui comme nous l’avons vu, sont un des principaux vecteurs de diffusion de cet idéal hyper-sexualisé. 
en ouverture et conclusion de ce que nous avons vu, nous pouvons transposer cela au chemin qui se dessine vers une nouvelle représentation féminine.
une femme qui s’implique, une femme qui initie. une femme qui vit sa sexualité librement, mais qui n’a pas à la subir. une femme qui ose et s’affirme. en réalité, il faut parler « des femmes », plurielles, indépendantes. non plus un idéal, mais des idéaux. 
les réseaux sociaux ont, certes, amplifier un phénomène de vision hyper-sexualisée des femmes. or cela a pris une telle ampleur, qu’il est devenu impossible de le nier. se développe alors l’effet inverse, la lutte contre cela, sur leurs principaux supports de diffusion. 
les réseaux sociaux sont aussi une plateforme d’expression, quand la violence, psychologique (via les actes d’autrui ou via notre rapport à notre corps induit par les images diffusées) ou physique, n’est pas écoutée et prise en compte. 
les réseaux sociaux ont la capacité de lancer un mouvement, de créer une communauté. avec un bon usage, le vecteur de dérive pour devenir celui d’une nouvelle émancipation, initiée par des mouvements précurseurs, antérieurs aux réseaux sociaux. revitaliser la lutte... pour un nouveau printemps.

#repost @bellamariaorsina (@get_repost)
・・・
as this 2018 🖤🤘is very soon coming to a close, it’s time to post this! 
dropped off social media early this year, posting only once in awhile, why? social media is no longer a social thing, a place to connect, a place to be happy for each other’s life experiences & events, but rather, marketing strategies, where authenticity is quite questionable, to play on your emotions to sell their products or services, a place of hating on, a place where people live their lives in the image of others instead of building on their own...lessons learnt in 2018 ✍️ get out!!! of anywhere where you don’t feel good in or are treated unfairly, when you go through a hard time, do take the time to take care of you & slowly get back up, becoming stronger, working on being the best you can be, and « live a private life » keeping your circle ⭕️ who are there for you, who wish you happiness & celebrate 🎊 you!!! when you surround yourself with positivity, positive things happen in your life!! when you stay in negative 👎 being surrounded with hatred, envy & abuse, it only destroys you, your dreams, your view of life! 
this life does have so much for you, so much love for you, your own beautiful story, just stay in the light of positivity 💡 and you will see it clearly!! reach for your stars⭐️✨!!!
#positivevibes #positivity #surroundyourselfwithpositivepeople #surroundyourselfwithgoodpeople #goafteryourdreams #getout #loveyourself #metoo
name: R.I.P.

as this 2018 🖤🤘is very soon coming to a close, it’s time to post this! 
dropped off social media early this year, posting only once in awhile, why? social media is no longer a social thing, a place to connect, a place to be happy for each other’s life experiences & events, but rather, marketing strategies, where authenticity is quite questionable, to play on your emotions to sell their products or services, a place of hating on, a place where people live their lives in the image of others instead of building on their own...lessons learnt in 2018 ✍️ get out!!! of anywhere where you don’t feel good in or are treated unfairly, when you go through a hard time, do take the time to take care of you & slowly get back up, becoming stronger, working on being the best you can be, and « live a private life » keeping your circle ⭕️ who are there for you, who wish you happiness & celebrate 🎊 you!!! when you surround yourself with positivity, positive things happen in your life!! when you stay in negative 👎 being surrounded with hatred, envy & abuse, it only destroys you, your dreams, your view of life! 
this life does have so much for you, so much love for you, your own beautiful story, just stay in the light of positivity 💡 and you will see it clearly!! reach for your stars⭐️✨!!!
#positivevibes #positivity #surroundyourselfwithpositivepeople #surroundyourselfwithgoodpeople #goafteryourdreams #getout #loveyourself #metoo

text:
it’s easy to make things look pretty (hello instagram) but reality is what i’m looking for. after listening to speakers and collaborating with my teams, i know one thing is true. we want truth. we want real.

gen z and millennials want to know reality more than pretty words, sugar coated messages and smiles that don’t go away.

truth is, there is hurt and pain all around us. #metoo #churchtoo.

the inside critic says don’t share. don’t post. don’t frown. but freedom says, who cares what they say. let your voice be heard.

shout loud your thoughts, feelings, hurts, injustices.

shout loud your passion, your anger, your opinions.

in love, let’s wrap our arms around each other in a world full of broken pieces, broken hearts. let judgement be far from our lips and let the critic inside us all be silenced.

be brave to tell your story. forget the appearance of it all. let your heart be heard.

let us all be led to light.

text:
so, time for some thoughts...
last night, i went over to someone’s house. let’s call him cory. this was supposed to be a chance to get to know one another, and see how we mesh as people. what it ended up being is me, lying in a bed terrified of saying “no” because i was scared of what he’d do. any requests or attempts to redirect the situation were pushed past or completely ignored. he was coercive and manipulative, bouncing between tender, kind, controlling, hungry, angry, and a myriad of other emotions. i’ve never been in a position where i was legitimately scared to say “no” as he dragged my hands where he wanted them to go.
to him, i was just a body, a delicious lay that he could sink his teeth into. he felt entitled to me, and made it evident that i was being unfair to him if i rejected his advances. he even tried to get me to have one of my partners come over once he found out they were physically his type. it got so bad i started crying, sobbing uncontrollably as i attempted to drag my pants back up my legs. instead of comforting me, he just told me to stop, and when i didn’t, he huffed over to my purse and dropped it next to me. “call your bf” he told me. 
i’d never been in this position before, unable to escape and watching everything i say in case it set him off...he never hit me, instead he made it very clear that he was in charge and it was in my best interest to cooperate.
the whole encounter was awful, but it reminded me that people are very different online, and men will often say whatever they need to as long as it gets them what they want. 
i know a lot of this encounter was my fault, but that doesn’t justify his actions.
hell of a learning curve.
#metoo

text:
#metooinmedicine

i never shared my story. why? for the reason that many other women failed to share- fear of retaliation, fear of perception, fear of professional harm - fear. furthermore, we all know medicine seems to lag about 20 years behind the rest of the world in social advancement.

my eyes were truly opened today at a watch (women at children’s national) seminar on sexual harassment in the work place. 
i am still quite low on the totem pole - i am in my 3rd year as an attending and assistant professor at a large academic hospital. yes, i am an attending, i am a professor, i do have grant funding - but the fact is i still have (hopefully) another 30-40 years left of my career in academic medicine. 
for that reason, when the rest of the world was sharing their #metoo stories - you may have noticed the women and men in medicine remaining relatively silent (with a few exceptions of course!). throughout my 18 years having an md by my name, i (most often unknowingly) was the brunt of sexism and what i now know is deemed sexual harassment. but i never spoke up. as we further specialize into our ultimate careers - it becomes incredibly apparent that our career communities become smaller and smaller. that fear of being the “outspoken” male or female keeps most of us quiet. this needs to end. as i write this i can remember innumerable side comments on my looks, my size, societal norms of being a woman, being “cute” - let me tell the world - when i am at work i am not “cute.” i am a badass pediatric critical care attending, i command a room when i am taking care of critically ill children, and i hustled to get grant funding less than 2 years into being an attending. the more we speak out, the more we force the culture of medicine to catch up to the rest of the world. .
i would like to say that i am very happy in my current job. i have a boss that supports me and i have colleagues that lift me up. but it wasn’t always this way. and that needs to change. 
so what’s your stance on #metooinmedicine ? are we ready for change? share your opinion, your stance or even your stories. 
#strongertogether
name: Anita, M.D., RYT-500

for that reason, when the rest of the world was sharing their #metoo stories - you may have noticed the women and men in medicine remaining relatively silent (with a few exceptions of course!). throughout my 18 years having an md by my name, i (most often unknowingly) was the brunt of sexism and what i now know is deemed sexual harassment. but i never spoke up. as we further specialize into our ultimate careers - it becomes incredibly apparent that our career communities become smaller and smaller. that fear of being the “outspoken” male or female keeps most of us quiet. this needs to end. as i write this i can remember innumerable side comments on my looks, my size, societal norms of being a woman, being “cute” - let me tell the world - when i am at work i am not “cute.” i am a badass pediatric critical care attending, i command a room when i am taking care of critically ill children, and i hustled to get grant funding less than 2 years into being an attending. the more we speak out, the more we force the culture of medicine to catch up to the rest of the world. .
i would like to say that i am very happy in my current job. i have a boss that supports me and i have colleagues that lift me up. but it wasn’t always this way. and that needs to change. 
so what’s your stance on #metooinmedicine ? are we ready for change? share your opinion, your stance or even your stories. 
#strongertogether

text:
ego - someone's ego is their sense of their own worth. for example, if someone has a large ego, they think they are very important and valuable.

we all have a sense of self worth. for better or worse, it is important that we realize how much we are worth to those around us. but when does it become a problem? when does our sense of self worth turn into self-importance and self centeredness? 
is your ego affecting people around you in a positive way? or is it self serving only to you? are you so self-centered that you will do anything to stroke that ego. even if it means crushing the self worth of those you come into contact with?

in my career as a model, this was an everyday experience. the men and even sometimes women in this industry were egotistical, and self serving. the drive to fulfill their own desires was the only goal. if you were collateral damage, so be it. -

you see, your ego is the justifier to your actions. one more time.... your ego is the justifier to your actions! you can justify anything you do if it pleases your ego. a photographer will mentally, sexually, verbally abuse a model. but ego tells him/her it’s part of the artistic process. an agent will knowingly and willingly put a model in a compromised position. but the ends justify the means, or at least that’s what ego tells them. there are many more instances in this arena, but it’s not exclusive only to fashion/modeling. -

my self-worth during my time modeling was at an all time low. i wasn’t the same person that i was going into it. years of being broken down to serve others egos took its toll on me. i compensated, for a low self-worth and projected my ego onto those around me. often not caring how it affected them. this is something i have worked on. keeping my self-esteem high but my ego in check. -

nobody’s ego is important enough to trample on another’s sense of self. nobody is so above the rest that consequences from their actions shouldn’t matter. how you treat people has ripple effects in this world. how has your ego affected those around you?

truth is inevitable.

#model #modeling #fashion #speakup #metoo #mentoo #timesup #modelalliance #selfworth #ego #love #mentalhealth

text:
el valor de una traqueotomía

vos y solo vos 
conocías el verdadero rostro
del desgarro.

para nosotrxs
la única preocupación 
era optar 
entre divinas y populares.

nos creímos esa historia:
el padre de un patito
con sonrisa entradora
y bailarinas de uniforme
al son de la comedia musical.

mientras tanto  te asfixiabas

y no había poción para cicatrizar
semejante herida nicaraguense.

hasta que tuviste 
el valor de una traqueotomía
y desnudar la voz
bastó para que 
millones de argentinxs
nos pusiéramos en tu lugar.

hoy latinoamérica
es un hashtag que nos duele

y tu relato
la insignia 
que te consagra  una heroína nacional. 🚫❎📣💪✊ #miracomonosponemos #metoo #noesno #thelmafardin #literatura #poesia #poemas #escritura #lector #nonoscallamosmas #fuerzamujeres #yositecreo

text:
tenía un par de postalitas para publicar esta semana, pero me quedé paralizada. 
perplexa. dolida. 
estuve viendo lo que pasó en argentina y sentí que hablar de cualquier otra cosa hubiera sido ignorarlo. 
me duele la piel cuando miro el video de thelma. 
me duele el alma cuando leo algunas respuestas o comentarios al respecto. de parte de hombres y mujeres. 
me duele la vida cuando identifico actitudes de machito en hombres que conozco. 
pero mi piel, mi alma y mi vida empiezan a sanar cuando veo, participo en o leo sobre el movimiento de mujeres. 
cuando escucho que madres y padres de varones se comprometen a criar a sus hijos como hombres, pero de los buenos. 
cuando siento toda esta sororidad multiplicarse. 
cuando entiendo que el futuro tiene cara de mujer. .
.
.
📆 diciembre 2018

text:
about a year ago i started making small changes that had a big impact.  one of the changes i made was drinking green juice.  once upon a time (about 367 days ago 😉), i would have never tasted the stuff let along love it!

this week has been an off week.  i had things come up and i didn’t get to the store to stock up on my veggies and fruit.  i find it amazing at the difference this made in my mood, energy levels and overall functioning.  i had my powder version on hand that i usually use when traveling.  it was ok, but not the same as the real deal.

i like to think of my green juice as my magic elixir.  i feel better when i am regularly drinking it.  my green juice is real simple - cucumbers, celery, granny smith apples, arugula, and ginger root.  although it is simple, it contains approximately 6-7 servings of veggies and fruit.  of course i feel great after drinking it - i’m providing my body with essential energy needs.  and, sometimes i choose to make up a green juice instead of having chocolate (shhh...don’t tell anyone!). when we begin to take care of ourselves, our bodies feel it.  we respond differently, are in a better mood, and just feel better.  what can you do to take better care of yourself? 😊

text:
you gotta love joseph’s story!
“from slave to the ruler of egypt in 7 simple steps”

here is his cv:

1-17 years old: favorite son of his father, jacob. his 10 brothers hate him.

17 yo: brothers want to kill him, but instead sell him as a slave to random nomads.

potiphar, a minister of the pharaoh, buys him and lets him slave away in his house. everything joseph does there is crowned by divine success.

28 yo: joseph is a handsome man and potiphar’s wife repeatedly tries to seduce him, but joseph is righteous and doesn’t touch what is not his.

as revenge, potiphar’s wife joins the #metoo movement and accuses him of sexual harassment. 
following the #ibelieveher ideology, where a woman is to be believed anything she says against a man, without proof or evidence (isn’t that sexist?), joseph is thrown into prison.

in his late 20’s joseph imagines his career to be somewhat different than sitting in a dark dungeon, but doesn’t lose faith and uses his skills to become the prison warden’s right-hand #career #milennials

30 yo: pharaoh has dreams which nobody can interpret. joseph can. he predicts 7 years of plenty following 7 years of famine. 
pharaoh appoints him as his right-hand. he becomes the second man in egypt, the center of human civilization of that time.

joseph develops an economical scheme to prevent worldwide famine. #logistics #publicpolicy

39: joseph is #rich&famous. reigns over egypt with the pharaoh. 
his brothers come to egypt to buy food. 
he forgives his brothers, not without playing a little game on them before. 👉🏻 isn’t it exciting how every scenario is already in the torah? that is why it’s not a history book, but a blueprint for a fulfilling life.

have a great week, everybody!

text:
when i first recognized that i could use creativity as a tool to tell segments of my story, it created the most incredible and illuminating shift in my world. for the first time in my life, i felt as though i had an outlet. a way of expressing myself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this form of expression didn't change my circumstances. it didn't magically make all of my hurts disappear. but i felt as though the next breath was slightly less jagged. i finally had a coping mechanism. a hand held out. a friend.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photography and creative writing have been lifelines for me. a way of giving a voice to some of my experiences, without the pressure of having to explain them. because explanation often requires justification, and then something is lost, further crushed inside.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
there are so many ways in which women are censored. we edit our existence because the world is still not ready to accept our multitudes. creativity helps to soften that editing process; it gives us a cloak of protection whilst also allowing us to be bare.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💜 thanks to @traumaandco for sharing my quote above (a section from my piece, creativity and the #metoo movement). also, a reminder that my new e-series begins january 1st. link in bio to find out more about creating courage: the heart of creative living. i'd love to have you join me ✨

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
there are so many ways in which women are censored. we edit our existence because the world is still not ready to accept our multitudes. creativity helps to soften that editing process; it gives us a cloak of protection whilst also allowing us to be bare.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
one plant that has so many skill’s and purpose’s in this life. i have myself used it for many reason’s. 
i self medicated back in the early 2000’s as it was frowned upon then. i was 16/17 but i had lived through some thing’s most don’t at that age, and was having bad thoughts. weed saved my life then. it helped me deal with; ptsd and trauma from teen rape’s, seasonal depression, insomnia, anxiety, ( i had trouble in school regarding my learning disabilities,) anorexia, pain aid for broken or dislocated bone’s (i now know i had/ have ehlers danlos syndrome #3 which is why i would hurt myself often when snowboarding.) back then i was not smoking always, just when i needed it and just enough to help me through. 
today i am a medical patient for rheumatoid arthritis and also for extreme anxiety, my path and journey has been long and hard. but i have gotten to be in a good place thanks to myself and the people in my life. and of course, with the help from this one plant. i have a deep love for marijuana and a special connection with it. 
consult your doctor for what is right for you, as this was my journey and path in life and may not be right you.❤️💛💚 #weedstagram420 #cloudsovercanada #instaweed #legalizedit #cannabiscommunity #cannabisculture #cannabis #marijuana #medicalmarijuana #medicalmarijuanapatient #cannamom #medicatedmom #puffpuffpass #420 #weed #iwillmarrymary #thc #highlife #liftedladies #staylifted #cannafam #stonerfam #metoo #depression #anxiety #anxietyrelief #rheumatoidarthritis #healingplant #ptsd #weed

・・・
on december 17 at judson memorial church, we remember sex workers who have died from violence. international day to end violence against sex workers was founded 15 years ago in san francisco by @anniesprinkled as a memorial and candlelight vigil for the victims of the seattle green river killer. the day calls attention to hate crimes committed against sex workers worldwide, as well as the need to remove the stigma, discrimination and indifference that contributes to violence against them. it is now observed globally in local vigils and gatherings. 
from the time i began my career in human sexuality, the rights of sex workers has been my passion. in 1985, a meeting took place at judson memorial church that connected me with margo st. james and the international sex workers’ rights movement. i have been active in that movement ever since. judson memorial church has been a long-time advocate for harm reduction and safe haven for sex workers, and the welcoming host of the nyc december 17 vigil for nearly a decade. i invite you to join me, members of judson, the sex worker community, and friends and allies as we remember the dead. rest in power.

you are welcome to participate in part or all of the evening’s events:

5pm -- the candle inscription and community-building session begins

7pm -- the open mic begins; reading of names, stories, songs, poetry and performances are encouraged.

9pm -- clean-up promptly begins

let us know if you want to be on the program and/or have relevant announcements, names and stories for us to honor and uplift on that day. 
more details about the nyc vigil are on our facebook page: 
http://bit.ly/dec17nyc2018

details about other global events are available at www.december17.org 
veronica vera
doctor of human sexuality

#december17 #17december #sexworker
#humanrights #endgenderbasedviolence #metoo #timesup #translivesmatter #queerlivesmatter #restinpower #decriminalizesexwork #respectnotrescue #sexpositive #pleasureactivism

text:
the hindu reports 
the third edition of the likho awards for excellence in media were presented on saturday, right after the second edition of the likho indian lgbtq media summit.
the awards in 10 categories covered print and digital journalism along with graphic art, film, radio, and advertising.

some of the winners were journalists alka dhupkar, chitra palekar, roshan kokane and r. raj rao. filmmaker onir won for his 2005 film my brother nikhil in a new category — the trailblazer — to honour an individual’s past works.

preceding the awards ceremony was the likho indian lgbtq media summit with four panels: ‘pitching lgbtq stories’ on queer roles in film and television; ‘cracking the regional media code’ to encourage cross-pollination of thoughts; ‘#lgbtqinmedia – being an out media person’ with several professionals recounting their experiences; and finally ‘beyond #metoo – creating equal, diverse, inclusive and safe media work places in india’. three months after the supreme court partially struck down section 377, decriminalising homosexuality, the conclave sought to draw awareness to the road ahead for the queer community. ashok row kavi, chairperson of the humsafar trust, focused on the atmosphere pre and post the verdict. media professional dipti agarwal noted how newsrooms have changed, while priya babu of the transgender resource network highlighted the issues of the trans community and called for a change in its representation in the media. journalist and politician apsarra reddy said, “for me, it is important to put my skill set and my talent out there. if people continue to judge me because of my gender, it’s their problem.” she continued, “to reclaim your space is very important and in the whole #metoo movement, women need to have a stronger voice.” the event also hosted a screening of short film cover story by director suhail abbasi. the day-long event was organised by bombay dost, india’s oldest lgbtq magazine and the humsafar trust in partnership with blued, a gay social networking app. the summit was organised to promote a fair and inclusive workplace for the lgbtq community.
#journalist #mumbai #india #lgbtq #life #work #award

text:
if someone in your life has experienced sexual trauma, then you may struggle with what to say and how to help that #survivor . you may also struggle with understanding certain parts of their story, or how they are dealing with it.
.
those thoughts and feelings are very common.
.
there is a page on my website called "how to support a survivor" to help you navigate this journey.
.
the words and actions of those in a survivor's life have a huge impact on that survivor and their healing. you have a vitally important role to play. click the link in my bio, select "supporters of #metoo survivors" and then scroll down for some resources to help you.
.
share this post with anyone you know who is trying to figure out how to help a survivor.
.
.
.

text:
✨ you might have noticed, i do think that digital activism can have an impact in real life but everyone does not agree!
➡️ for my last post for #digipoluclouvain, i wanted to share some of the critics made on digital activism.
🔹 some people use the term “slacktivism” to talk about cyber-activism. slacktivism is the contraction between “slacker” and “activism” and it means that digital activism would actually be only clicks done by lazy people [40]. some people even argue that slacktivism could be “harmful to the larger process of civic renewal” [41]. digital activism could be dangerous because it is only seen as actions made by individuals and not anymore as a collective protest, so the impact would be less effective [42].
🔹 another critic made by peter levine is that cyber-activism can make a change but not in the long-term : “online campaigns may all prove evanescent and lack an ability to handle and overcome valid criticisms or lack the infrastructure necessary to invite and train youth from apolitical networks to replace current leaders the way traditional political organizations could.” [43]
🔹 a third critic is that it is not easy to evaluate the impact of cyber-activism [44].
▪️ i will argue by asking is it really easier to evaluate the impact of offline activism? some offline campaigns’ impact can be measured (the civic right movement for example) as online campaigns’ impact (#metoo) can be too.
▪️ thinking about that, i will also say that it depends on what activists ask for. during the civil rights movement, black people were demanding formal rights the states refused to give them [45]. but #metoo or #blacklivesmatter do not per se ask for formal rights, because violence is already punished by the law, equality between gender is already inscribed in the law [46]. what #metoo, #blacklivesmatter and many other movements ask nowadays is mostly a change of mentality, which can be slow and hard to measure.
📸 https://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_58c07355e4b0ed7182699a54

text:
"remember when they told you i was too black for ya?
and now my black poppin' like a bra-strap on ya
i was kicked out, said i'm too loud
kicked out, said i'm too proud
but all i really ever felt was stressed out
kinda like my afro when it's pressed out" -janell monáe

in highschool (before it was cool) i didn't participate in the national anthem or pledge of allegiance,
i refused to speak lies and i knew not everyone was free.
and still to this day we are not free.
we as in you and me.

this is 2018
women are still being assaulted/raped and faulted for what they wear or don't wear and do.
black people are at fault and punished for being black.
immigrants are treated like trash.
gays can't even buy cakes.
so when are we free?
let's aim for 2019.
let's come together in solidarity.
let's end this foolishness.
let's be free like for real.
i am here to tell you, you cannot hate me for being black but you can hate me for me.
if you cannot control your penis, you must control your penis because you cannot control me.
if you can't stand to look at a gay couple look for compassion. 
and if you are assaulted for any or all of the above you were not asking for it and you don't deserve it.
if hate is what drives you;

drive somewhere else. ✌️ because #wematter

text:
book #7
frances e. mascia-lees & nancy johnson black ‘gender and anthropology’
2000

academic—each of the nine chapters feels like a week’s lesson plans for a 10 week lecture course—it is a good starting point and very worth your time read in the #metoo era; despite the brevity each section is packed with information and thoughtful explanation of many theories by numerous anthropologist.

you learn to think for yourself by having multiple sources in-part that in-total add up to the possible truth (no one theory can tell us why our society or any society is the way it is, or why women, minorities, and non-western peoples are represented/discussed/treated the way they have been). critical thinking skills are honed in this (as a first foray into gender studies ‘gender and anthropology’ is for many readers’ the first steps into an understanding of why humanity’s many cultures, historical and contemporary, have and maintain its view of women, their importance in society, and their role within it.

by the time you arrive at chapter six it dawns on you that no one theory single-handedly is an easy explanation for cross-culture explanation for gender roles; all of these theories in part yet combined tell the story of why we are the way we are.

there is no single easy fit—although friedrich engels comes close (centuries before the rest of euro-centric “civilization” caught-up). one of my university course reads i neglected finishing—but still managed to earn an a in the class. don’t follow my lead. read books at the time you get them. so a years later you don’t have finish as part of your list of “the books that got away”. #mybookclubfor1 #10000bookbucketlistchallenge #greatamericanread #whattoread #bookworm #genderstudies

text:
in 1877 two committed teachers and a dedicated student made history in chile!⠀
. ⠀
when isabel lebrun and antonia tarragó founded two schools for girls in the xix century, they faced a major challenge: girls were not allowed to go to university in chile. no matter how well their students performed, their education would have to end with high school. and so, these two teachers fought and lobbied until the amunategui decree was passed in 1877, giving finally all women the right to attend university. their students could go to college. ⠀
now, a monument stands in downtown santiago to honor the lives, work and contribution of these two incredible teachers.⠀
.⠀
it would take another 10 years for the first woman to graduate university. eloisa diaz had studied in isabel lebrun's school and aspired to tear down barriers. when the amunategui decree was passed she enrolled in university but, because of prejudices at the time, had to attend classes with her mother. still, she persisted and in 1887 she became the first woman in chile to obtain a university degree. eloisa diaz was the first female doctor not just in chile but in all of latin america. ⠀
.⠀
the feminist history of santiago and chile is rich and full of stories like that of isabel lebrun, antonia tarrago and eloisa diaz. join our feminist tour a au tako'a to discover these and more stories hidden in the streets of santiago. ⠀ .⠀
#feminism #travelrecommendation #travelrecommendations #travelblogger #femaletraveler #metoo #niunamenos #womentraveling

text: i love my @with.love.d bracelet so much. i loved choosing my own word. thursday night was difficult because of a #metoo thing that happened. i kept reading my bracelet reminding myself that i would be ok because i was #resilient - that helped. i love that the letters are hand stamped so they aren’t perfect because that reminds me that no one is perfect. i also love that it stays in place above my wrist bone and it isn’t tight. but what i really love are the hanging charms. usually those bug the heck out of me but these are the perfect length. they don’t rub against my hand when i type on my computer. woo hoo. this is just #theperfectbracelet i can’t wait to order another one (or two) for #stackingbracelets #standupcollective

text:
"with a growing number of radio stations wanting to ax the playing of the christmas tune "baby, it's cold outside," some louisville radio stations are fighting back by, you guessed it, playing it, not just from time-to-time, but repeatedly, on a never-ending loop.
classic hits station waky-fm will be playing "baby, it's cold outside," on a continuous repeating loop beginning sunday morning, said chris randolph, one of the station's disc jockeys. meanwhile, waky, on 103.5 and 100.1 fm, will also be playing different versions of the song over and over for several hours on sunday.
randolph put out this statement:
"everyone just seems so sensitive to the lyrics of the song, & we just thought everybody should calm down," randolph said. "these stations pulling the song, it's absolutely ludicrous."
controversy arose around the christmas tune, written byfrank loesser in 1944, when it started getting banned by radio stations around the country after its lyrics were attacked for promoting date rape & were deemed inappropriate with the #metoo movement happening. 
however, if the song's detractors were trying to silence and shun it off the airwaves, the exact opposite reaction has happened, with the tune making a comeback in several markets after listeners voted to keep the song on the airwaves. the song is now at close to 11 million views on youtube.
lee cagle, operations manager of summitmedia says he's "not had one single complaint about the song," adding "i personally think people are looking for things to be offended by." cagle pointed to complaints that another classic christmas tune & film, "rudolph the red-nosed reindeer," features bullying & sexism. "i'm waiting to see which other song people start complaining about," he added. "we don't take life too seriously, & we attract that type of listener," randolph said. "it's all just out of fun.""
@doctorzorters

text: for me looking back, my abuser has been in my life for years. having to realize that nothing was what i thought it was and accepting that every memory of my teenage years is tainted by him weather he was hurting  me or just present for those moments is a painful process. to see your whole high school experience shattered and to not be able to talk about old times because it’s too painful, because he was present for all of them. i’m slowly getting to a point where i can talk about it again sometimes. it’s not easy. do your best . it’s okay if you can’t. just make new beautiful memories without him, in spite of him, the best way to win is to be happy without him. you can do it. i believe in you. #survivorsupport  #metoo #ptsd #pushingforward #takingmypowerback #mymemoriesnotyours

text:
some words, some thoughts... inspired by a conversation i had with @jmhayleypoetry...
.
.
if you feel offended, you is me and maybe you is you as well, maybe not. whatever. .
.
no, i don’t think every abuse or attack can be blamed on men, and neither on women. i believe that it’s very dangerous thing to blame any kind of “group” and i think we all have our own responsibilities. that doesn’t change the fact that there are horrible people, and that a lot of women have been through horrible things that they can not be blamed for in any kind of way. but it is too easy to blame all men. i’ve seen to many women playing a victim, when they easily could have made other choices, again not always. believe me i’ve come from dark places and i have seen men using their power against a lot of broken girls, but those are not the girls crying for free abortion pills. those are girls crying not even for justice, they are working their ass of while heartbroken just so they can have a new start. .
.
coming up soon is a letter. a letter about feminism and how the #metoo movement is one i no longer want to invest my time in. has feminism become something that i no longer seem to understand? even though i refuse to not believe in equality of the sexes and will always stand for the real definition of feminism. i wonder though; is this movement still about that definition or did it become propaganda; a woman’s cry not for help, but for attention. not for the kind of attention that will help make real, honest and big differences and improve the lives of so many broken and hurt women.. no, just enough attention for their little broken egos to heal. is that today’s feminism? - also, how much responsibility do we take as women? are we all victims or did we start the games and lost control? .
.
.
.
 #poem #words #prose #poetrycommunity #writers #poets  #writer #quotes #writerscommunity #proza #words #shewolf #writtenwords #writing #writer #writersofinstagram #analizapoetry #diaryofanaliza

text:
i can swear, i can joke
i say what's on my mind
if i drink, if i smoke
i keep up with the guys

text:
i'm about to go awf... one of the reasons why so many black women find feminism grotesque is because it. does. not. serve. us. at. all. worse, we actually lose far more than we can afford by allowing non-black women to reach that class ceiling by standing on the bridge called our backs.

this woman right here has made a catwalk out of #metoo. she will show up to the kavanaugh hearing, tell tamika mallory what to do, and then play doey eyed deer in headlights when asked to speak on behalf of a black woman who is incarcerated for defending herself from a sexual assaulter.

she moves this way in the name of 'intersectionality'. people applaud her for this role. 
y'all really let 2/3 of the cast of charmed hijacked gender liberation and feminism (even though feminism was already trash, but, whatever). #feminism #whitefeminism #alyssamilano #intersectionalfeminism #intersectionality #whitefeminists

text: so me weighing in on this (disclaimer i only saw this portion of the interview that’s been all over the web), but do i think ebro was trying to have a viral/ birdman type of moment? no😒. these days every bird and duck sees something viral and they’re shouting “clout chaser” and “storyline” and “trying to go viral” like they don’t sound ridiculous. there is no way @oldmanebro could have anticipated that response. ebro brought up a very expected topic to kodak (who might be a rapist). the celebrity handled it childishly and the thing blew up. i think ebro should have been a little more patient with kodak, but if you catch me on a bad day and some stranger tries to tell me what i should and shouldn’t be doing...i’m burning everything to the ground. kodak has a problematic history when it comes to women and the law so he either has to expect these questions or get his team to manage them for him in advance. i’m rolling my eyes deeply at all the comments i’ve seen saying “ebro should have warned him before asking him that question”. y’all clearly don’t get how media works. ebro never even asked him a real question. he basically said “i know u have these charges u can’t speak on, this is a serious issue hopefully we can speak on it later.” then they crossed swords. i watched kodak get torn apart after making the derogatory comments about dark skinned girls, i sympathize that kodak is probably dealing with growing up and having his own skin insulted over and over and all the people jumping to the defense of black women calling him “an ugly black roach” were part of the problem. as much as a sympathize with kodak i want the culture to have less sympathy for the message of self-hate, rape, over promotion of drug use and general ignorance. i would love to be able to lift up a young brother like kodak without condoning their bullshit. so in the end stop supporting nonsense. kodak acted unprofessionally that’s the end of the story. one thing celebs lose is all of the checks and balances that help you grow. everyone agrees with anything they say, and if you ain’t a real one you can fall into it. we’re not doing him any favors by d*ckriding. #kodakblack #kodak #ebro #hot97

text: today our popup @aspenartcollective @aspensnowmass opens.  it’s been a year since i started the group and about 3 moths since we incorporated and became an llc.  i never thought i would own a business, let alone two.  the aspen art collective has a lot of legs: we collaborate with others in the name of local art from real estate to interior design to popup opportunities and fairs.  the possibilities honestly feel endless. come by snowmass base village today and check out @clarityelise_wovens installation in building 6 next to the limelight hotel and outdoor ice rink. the building’s grand opening is at 5:00 pm there will be free food and drank 🤤 #aspenartcollective #aspensnowmass #graydigital @grayconsulting.digital #voiceofthemountains 📸 @momomitchell #skicolorado #metoo #aspen #colorado #subarusnow #subaruambassador
