i went to see @nineinchnails tonight at the @hollywoodpalladium . i've never seen @treznor before. i was super excited. the night opened with @the_soft_moon & @jesusandmarychain . exquisite . definitely enjoying myself. until about 3ish hours in, the dude next to me decided to feel me up and grab my ass. i thought it was my husband but when i turned around it was a dude in a ponytail. i'd been standing next to him all night. i slapped his hand away and he said 'oh sorry' i held in my rage and hated every moment of joy he experienced. i spent a lot of money on these tickets and i didn't want that taken away. well, it was already taken from me. i couldn't enjoy anything after that. he stepped away to get a drink and i told his girlfriend what he did to me. she said 'if that happened, slap him.' if!!!??? yeah it happened! when he came back, i confronted him. he said he was just saying hi. i said, ' do you know how you say hi? with your fucking face!' ooooh sorry. yeah, sorry! he was escorted out during the last song, 'hurt'. how appropriate. i was left in a teary mess because someone was saying hi. how is this still happening?????!!! how are women still defending this behavior! i spent a lot of money on this experience and it was taken from me. this is what i will remember.  i'm so upset and there is no justice here.

text: see what people are saying about candy apple butterscotch, #newauthor rebecca macceile’s debut publication. “this is an impactful read if you have ever experienced any sort of abuse. i appreciate the author’s candor and willingness to write with such openness. she takes responsibility for herself as much as she describes the lasting effects of trauma.” “it is worth the read. it’s about a woman empowered and, my god, that is a wonderful thing indeed.” “the author gets to the point while still painting a very clear and definite picture for the readers and i love that. the accounts of the trauma are laid out in such a way that you know what’s happening and are able to imagine it but you aren’t bombarded with intense graphic imagery, which i appreciate as a survivor myself. would definitely recommend!” “this amazingly written gem takes you inside the author's world and keeps you there, making you feel like a discreet "bug on the wall." i could not put it down.” “i wish everyone would write a memoir. it would be so much easier to understand people. i haven’t been through anything as violent or traumatic, but i think this story is relatable in a lot of ways. it just makes me see a lot of things differently in every day life. it’s a big eye opener.” #onsalenow at the #linkinbio. #kindle and #paperback versions available! also for members of #amazonprime, candy apple butterscotch is available in the #kindlelendinglibrary as well as through #kindleunlimitedbooks! that’s right you can read for #free. #nonfictionbooks #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #kindlestoryteller2018  #kindledirectpublishing #onsalenow #paperback #kindlelendinglibrary #bookrecommendations #indieauthor #authorsofinstagram #amazon #readforfreekll now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books go entirely toward my #holiday #charity #fundraiser benefiting the #afsp you can find more info on rebeccasbookshop.com

text:
are you a teen passionate about ending sexual and gender-based violence? 
the firecracker foundation is recruiting self-identified survivors of sexual violence and allies to survivors of sexual violence who are in 10th or 11th grade to its new program, sisters in strength - lansing.  individuals who apply should share a vision for ending violence, desire to build sisterhood/siblinghood (community), and willingness to advocate for change.

link to more information and to apply in the bio.

this is a youth organizing program with a focus on both healing and organizing.

while this program is open to all teen survivors of sexual trauma and their allies, the firecracker foundation will prioritize the applications of teens of color, lgbtq2sia* teens, teens with disabilities and other marginalized groups in the lansing area. 
sisters in strength – lansing is an expansion of the firecracker foundation’s current teen club programming utilizing an adapted version of the sisters in strength (sis) curriculum developed by girls for gender equity - gge, based in brooklyn, new york, and the national me too movement - #metoo. this program is possible through funding provided by the the new york women's foundation and the girls innovate fund and is one of two pilot #metooteen programs in the country.

#metoo #metoomovement #youthorganizer #endsexualviolence
#endgenderbasedviolence 
#sparkhealing #truthtopower #internship #lovelansing #healing #community #opportunity #lgbtq #disabilityjustice #indigineousyouth #latinxyouth [image description: three black teens embrace and smile in white shirts]
name: The Firecracker Foundation
tweet_full:
are you a teen passionate about ending sexual and gender-based violence? 
the firecracker foundation is recruiting self-identified survivors of sexual violence and allies to survivors of sexual violence who are in 10th or 11th grade to its new program, sisters in strength - lansing.  individuals who apply should share a vision for ending violence, desire to build sisterhood/siblinghood (community), and willingness to advocate for change.

link to more information and to apply in the bio.

this is a youth organizing program with a focus on both healing and organizing.

while this program is open to all teen survivors of sexual trauma and their allies, the firecracker foundation will prioritize the applications of teens of color, lgbtq2sia* teens, teens with disabilities and other marginalized groups in the lansing area. 
sisters in strength – lansing is an expansion of the firecracker foundation’s current teen club programming utilizing an adapted version of the sisters in strength (sis) curriculum developed by girls for gender equity - gge, based in brooklyn, new york, and the national me too movement - #metoo. this program is possible through funding provided by the the new york women's foundation and the girls innovate fund and is one of two pilot #metooteen programs in the country.

#metoo #metoomovement #youthorganizer #endsexualviolence
#endgenderbasedviolence 
#sparkhealing #truthtopower #internship #lovelansing #healing #community #opportunity #lgbtq #disabilityjustice #indigineousyouth #latinxyouth [image description: three black teens embrace and smile in white shirts]

text:
#parte1 de 2 
#diciembre18 .
.
.

en el cielo 
lo cósmico se muestra la escena de la vida en el mundo.
es tal cual todo lo que estamos viviendo  desde lo individual a lo macro, lo universal. 
es impresionante la gente con la que tuve contacto éste año desde junio 2018 hasta la fecha y ver los ciclos de evolución de cada un@ y de todes.  trabajo mucho con los sueños y meditaciones de la gente que confía en mí a quienes agradezco desde lo más pronfundo de mi ser por la confianza ⭐✨ y much@s han vivenciado y soñado inundaciones reales o desde el inconsciente. 
soñaron con inundaciones! y/o
soñaron que corría el agua...
soñaron  a una persona que l@s había hecho sufrir mucho...
se les rompió el calefón o la caldera,  o el termotanque.
se les inundó la calle, 
desbordó el río... o desbordaron en llanto... sin saber el por qué.

y fíjate todo lo que llovió éste año. 🌧️•cada marcha por poner a accionar ley del aborto libre y gratuito.... llovió. 🌦️•partido river boca 🙄 que aunque pueda causar risa ( vos sabés bien cómo nos representan ambos equipos arquetípicos de lo argentino) y llovió. y salió el "arco iris" posterior. 🌬️🌈 ⛈️•el martes 11 que saliera a la luz la denuncia de violacion de una actriz menor de 16 años por un "famoso actor, atractivo, carismático y padre de familia" (⚡gran arquetipo #♂️ de la otra cara de la luna, el tipo es escorpio y con venus en tránsito se hace justicia #♏ #♀️) con el respaldo de muchas mujeres y también hombres... y ese día el cielo estaba iluminado por el sol de sagitario "justicia divina" con la luna en acuario "cambiar lo 'pre establecido'" se ilumina la verdad guardada femenina....desde venus que si te acordás estuvo retrogrado y ahora está directo en #escorpio
.
.
.
💜♀️♂️❤️ gracias 🦋

text:
self medicating only prolongs your mental healths healing.. .constructive clean healing works alot better xo 
my struggles 26 years ago lost and unsure how to deal with my childhood trauma having constant night terrors and all i wanted was for them to stop.
i wish i found faith and hope sooner which is why i'm here trying to inspire others to live the best versions of themselves and never let a trauma define who you are. you can be who ever you want..! xo

p.s. bititis was my married name years ago but i am no longer married to that person. most of my work i submitted in 2002. i won an award and published in america.

henry died because of dairy. he died because the industry demanded his life be seen as a 'waste product'.

.
we desperately tried to resuscitate you baby as you were unconcious. we tried so so hard to save you. i'm so sorry.
.
your grave was so so beautiful henry. i wasnt allowed to be there as you were buried as my soul couldn't take it and my friends watched me deteriorate but @_counting_sheep__  @micvvtla @j.e.b.e @floyd.269 and ben took such beautiful care of you.
.
i sit by your grave now in the morning and have coffee with you. i tell you i will never ever stop fighting. i will never ever stop exposing these industries and these places because of babies like you. the 750,000 'bobby calves' we kill every year in australia alone.
.

text:
tw: rape, sexual assault 
it was the sixth week of lucy’s freshman year, and she was dancing at a college party. she eventually went back to the dorm room of an athlete. “i remember knowing in my head, somehow, you had to scream “no” or yell “stop” at least three times. and because i didn’t do that, i thought, well, i can’t say this is sexual assault,” said lucy. “he was a student athlete, so i never officially reported it. and i knew if i did that it would just be an uphill fight.”
lucy grew up in a family that centered around big 10 sports, and she chose to go to her father’s alma mater. “having been raised a sports fan, i heard plenty of stories where ‘athletes at the peak of their careers’ were being ‘accused’ of rape, and then i saw the victims trashed in the press. i did not want that to be me.” still, lucy took steps to receive medical care after the assault, such as getting tested for stis at the university health clinic. she had a negative experience with the examining physician that ultimately contributed to her sense of shame, and fear of not being believed. “society told me this wasn’t a big deal, and it was my fault. and that’s how i felt.” lucy faced challenges with depression, substance abuse, and anxiety as a result of the assault. she sought counseling and was able to complete her degree, but many years later was still suffering. she lost her voice—a struggle that would be difficult for any survivor, but was heartbreaking to a professional singer like lucy. “i knew the therapy to get my [vocal cords working again] was to tell my story… but it wasn’t easy to talk about.” donate to rainn: fundraise.rainn.org/25sweaterss

text:
food justice isn’t just about cleaner watersheds, eradicating factory farming or more $$ in the pockets of the real stewards of the land; small organic and permaculture minded farmers and ranchers.  it’s about  gender equality too, in all realms of this movement.  shout out to @ediblesf for publishing this story.  over the years, i have asked most of the women who have worked in various food service departments at the co-op if they have experienced sexual harassment or discrimination in the greater reno food industry.  not to my surprise, all of the responses sounded a lot like corbina grieco’s when she was interviewed for the edible sf featured article, “like most young women in kitchens i endured by playing along and/or keeping my mouth shut.” does that sound familiar?  in order for women to thrive in this male dominated industry we must pretend like things don’t happen. 
things are changing, slowly but surely.  take for instance the james beard restaurant awards... everyone knows that they are a big deal for restaurants across the country, and this year the judges were asked to think a little broader than they have in the past. the judges were asked to, “when considering the candidacy of a person or restaurant, bear in mind that award winners are held up as role models. if you have concerns about a chef, restaurateur or beverage professional, or about the culture around a restaurant or restaurant group, leave the person or business out of your nominations.” this as more and more awareness is being drawn to sexual harassment in the restaurant industry. and the result? 40% of nominees were female, up 13% from the year before, where only a quarter of nominations went to female chefs and restauranteurs. @beardfoundation 
if the fundamentals of food systems are going to change then articles like this need to be written, along with one from the james beard foundation’s webpage: “we need to support women in the restaurant industry” - check it out 🥰 (link in bio)
https://www.jamesbeard.org/blog/we-need-to-support-women-in-the-restaurant-industry
 #metoo

text:
part 2 "trapped in the closet"

so we meet and physically he is not my type. but i tell myself don't judge a book by it's cover. he seemed a little off and nervous. as we sat and talked this guy begins to pull my arm hairs! i'm like don't do that. he says he's sorry and that it's a habit and he plays with his daughter that way. 
i want to run and leave him sitting there, but i ignored my first mind and just said maybe he's being odd because he's nervous. 
so i proceed to date this man. there are a lot of crazy moments with him. there is one where we are almost killed by a speeding car some loser carjacked. then there is the time where i met his crazy narcissistic cop sister. but what i'm writing about now is when he made me get in a closet and forced me not to come out. 
i had no idea that his elderly mother was home and he had invited me to spend the night. day came and it's a few days before christmas. his cop sister wants him to go shopping. this guy grabs me out of bed, tells me quickly my mom doesn't know you are here, get your ass in the closet and stay there until i get back. 
#metoo #abusiverelationship #bipolar #bipolardisorder #storytimethread #storytime

#repost @badasscrossstitch with @get_repost
・・・
via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action 
4. contact gov bill haslam’s office and voice your thoughts 1st floor, state capitol nashville, tn 37243 (615) 741-2001 
5. his instagram @governorbillhaslam (remember, he is considering clemency so let’s honor and encourage that) 
6. watch the video: me facing life: cyntoia’s story - google it - it’s on @pbs and you can watch it online. ——————
update:  original art by <<<< @janaillustration >>>follow her! her work is perfection. 
i have tried so hard to find out who made the original piece that i used to stitch this. if you know, please let me know so that i can cite. ——— #blacklivesmatter #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #metoo #justice #freecyntoia #clemencyforcyntoia #resist 
#blm #cyntoiabrown

text: i’m a lover, not a fighter. i don’t like to argue or have controversy with anyone. while it is possible to have a disagreement without exchange of angry words, if a person is unreasonable or argumentative, i’m out. i don’t do abuse in any form. you can only give so many chances. jokes, shade, pettiness, disrespect, yelling, delusion, gossip, revenge or lies. it’s abuse. period. not taking it, nor dishing it out. it is not cruel to end relationships. it is self preservation. if i don’t protect myself, no one will. as a survivor, i’ve learned to follow my gut. it never fails. we should all take heed. there is no relationship worth your personal safety or happiness. love doesn’t bully and it should never hurt. ever. #survivor #survivors #metoo #noabuse #selfpreservation #standingtall #standingfirm #riseabove #lover #empath #lockedandloaded #lovernotfighter #loversonly #livingwell #healthymindset #healthyoutlook #live #love #laugh #befree #innerpeace #peace #zen #mindset #lesbrownquotes #lesbrown #motivated #healed #strong #shazzinthecity 💪🏾🙌🏾😎

text:
@regran_ed from @galaxy4peace -  earlier today, we joined @awloint and @yalinetworklag on the #womendecide awareness walk to raise awareness and discuss issues around women's participation in politics. 
____________
to change the narratives, there is urgent need to accelerate equal participation of women in decision-making in the household and at the community level through adequate enlightenment, beginning at a tender age and making sure to reach the grassroots level so that no one is left behind.

and to promote women’s participation as voters and candidates in electoral processes and supporting women’s representation in governance institutions, including constitutional committees, electoral offices, public administrations, galaxy4peace strongly calls for more collaboration of stakeholders to develop and implement advocacy strategies, and policies that will facilitate in changing the narratives.

text:
part 3
"trapped in the closet"

so he forces me in the closet and tells me to stay in there until he gets back. i insist that i want to just leave. he twists my arm and tells me don't fucking come out, he loves me and he'll be back and closes the door. once i'm in i'm to scared and shocked to even make a noise. this side of him came out of nowhere. 
i'm in the closet and i'm scared, i have to pee. i try not to move so no one hears me. i feel if his mother hears me she will be frightened. k also am scared that if he finds out he could really hurt me. 
time passes and i noticed the day turns to night. i can tell through a small crack in the door. suddenly i hear footsteps coming up stairs, the bedroom door opens. i freeze, too scared to breathe. it was him. he slowly opens the door. "aww poot" he says with a weird grin calling me my nickname he gave me. "come out pootie". he grabs me by my wrist and walks me slowly out of the closet. i start crying, without making a sound. i see i had been in that closet for 7 hours..7 insane hours!! he kisses me on the forehead and makes me sit down on the bed. i say i have to use the bathroom. he frowns and says bring your ass on. he sneaks me downstairs to the bathroom. 
after this twisted event i end up stuck spending christmas there. i will share next time how that went.

#bipolarrelationship #metoo #abuse #abusiverelationship #mentalillness #storytimethread #storytime #realshit #reallife #bipolar #bipolardisorder

text:
hello everyone, i am sorry i haven't been as active since being released from the hospital. i elected to admit myself to a partial hospitalization program and intensive outpatient program to better help me in my adjustment from the hospital, for further management of my medications, and to better process my trauma. i want to make sure this remains a space where i post because i feel like i have something valuable to contribute, not out of obligation. i am trying not to feel guilty and just respect that i need and deserve self care right now.

thank you all for your lovely and supportive messages. also, if you have sent me a dm and haven't gotten a response it is nothing personal at all. i receive many messages, most of which include disclosures of some kind. for the sake of my own mental health i respond when i am in the best place of mind to do so. the fact that people trust me with their trauma is incredible, humbling and not something i take lightly. you are all so incredibly strong and inspiring to me. 
comment below: what was your favorite lesson? what is your biggest lesson(s) learned as a survivor? 
leave a 💜 if you read this far.

text: “we need to act on the principle of tikkun olam (repairing the world). if we organize, we can change the world.” ✊🏻🙌🏻✊🏻#feminist #civilrights & #reproductiverights #activist & political strategist #heatherbooth was born #onthisday in 1945. as a teen she participated in #freedomsummer in mississippi in 1964 from which “i took with me the lesson that you need to stand up for justice and help others in need – a lesson that resonated deeply with my #jewish beliefs.” from there she went on to found the first campus women's movement organization in 1965 and began jane, one of the country's first abortion counseling services. she campaigned for childcare, health care, and women's rights in many arenas. in 1989, she directed the national march for women's lives. in 2000, she was the director of the naacp national voter fund, which helped to increase african american election turnout by nearly 2 million voters. she has consulted for a variety of social change and political groups that have included moveon.org, the national committee to preserve social security and medicare, and the national council of la raza. #herstory #womenmakinghistory #changemaker #womenshistory #womenwholead #inspirationalwomen #inspiringwomen #metoo #femaleleaders #shesbeautifulwhenshesangry #feministart #watercolorillustration #rebelgirl #courageouswomen #girlboss #shepersisted #womeninpolitics #womenyoushouldknow @womenmakemovies #womensmarch

＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。

text: сотрудники социальной сети instagram проанализировали поставленные пользователями смайлики, геолокации и хештеги и опубликовали итоги 2018 года. об этом сообщается на официальном сайте instagram. таким образом, самой счастливой геолокацией instagram признал диснейленд в токио, так как больше всего счастливых смайликов в 2018 году пользователи ставили именно под фотографиями из японского диснейленда. также эксперты назвали самый популярный фильтр для лица: им стал фильтр с сердечками на глазах. а, например, самыми часто используемыми хештегами в 2018 году были #metoo, #timesup и #marchforourlives. в ноябре сотрудники британской ассоциации потребителей which? составили рейтинг самых безопасных стран для путешествий. специалисты проанализировали 20 самых популярных туристических направлений по четырем критериям: уровень преступности, угроза здоровью, вероятность теракта и стихийных бедствий. самой безопасной страной по всем параметрам стала исландия.

text:
@nau.shit ・・・
#metoo
i was molested when i was in 6th grade by my cousins uncle. i used to live in a joint family household. so, whenever he came to visit my cousins family, he would somehow manage to find me alone. at first, i didn’t know exactly what was going on or what he was trying to do, but i tried to stop him every time because i knew it wasn’t right. it wasn’t something i wore or i didn’t give him “the signal” or i didn’t ask for it. i was a fucking 12 year old kid going through puberty. he would grab my breast and twist them as hard as he can. i would try to push him away and run away from him, but nothing seemed to work. it was a feeling that i’ll never forget. i would cry in pain at night, but it wasn’t the pain of my tender breast that made me cry, it was the pain in my heavy heart. and i would ask god “why me?” then be thankful to god because i didn’t get raped. 
i finally decided to tell my mom and the look on her face was unforgettable. i can already see she felt helpless. she was silent, then i said “ammu please can i call 911 and get him arrested?” and my mom said “no.” at that very moment my heart broke into so many pieces that i became numb. it hurt the most because i felt betrayed by my own mother. she didn’t want to “ruin” my reputation or my future, especially because i didn’t have a father. she didn’t want anyone to question our family because we come from a “well known, respected family”. i was angry at my mom for couple of days, then i put myself in her shoes and saw what she was going through as a mother. my mom got scared, being a widow and an immigrant with three kids in a bengali society was not easy. my mom loves me with everything and she became my shield. so, i kept my mouth shut for all these years. 
i was contemplating if i should post this or not. i kept asking myself, what would people say? what if my future family doesn’t accept me for this? what if no one believes me? then, i realized that’s the exact reason why my mom never said anything and i didn’t want to be that person. i have every right to speak up for myself. i am more than just a body. i am strong. ______________
to be featured be sure to follow @crownthebrown_ 👑

i was molested when i was in 6th grade by my cousins uncle. i used to live in a joint family household. so, whenever he came to visit my cousins family, he would somehow manage to find me alone. at first, i didn’t know exactly what was going on or what he was trying to do, but i tried to stop him every time because i knew it wasn’t right. it wasn’t something i wore or i didn’t give him “the signal” or i didn’t ask for it. i was a fucking 12 year old kid going through pubey. he would grab my breast and twist them as hard as he can. i would try to push him away and run away from him, but nothing seemed to work. it was a feeling that i’ll never forget. i would cry in pain at night, but it wasn’t the pain of my tender breast that made me cry, it was the pain in my heavy hea. and i would ask god “why me?” then be thankful to god because i didn’t get raped. 
i finally decided to tell my mom and the look on her face was unforgettable. i can already see she felt helpless. she was silent, then i said “ammu please can i call 911 and get him arrested?” and my mom said “no.” at that very moment my hea broke into so many pieces that i became numb. it hu the most because i felt betrayed by my own mother. she didn’t want to “ruin” my reputation or my future, especially because i didn’t have a father. she didn’t want anyone to question our family because we come from a “well known, respected family”. i was angry at my mom for couple of days, then i put myself in her shoes and saw what she was going through as a mother. my mom got scared, being a widow and an immigrant with three kids in a bengali society was not easy. my mom loves me with everything and she became my shield. so, i kept my mouth shut for all these years. 
i was contemplating if i should post this or not. i kept asking myself, what would people say? what if my future family doesn’t accept me for this? what if no one believes me? then, i realized that’s the exact reason why my mom never said anything and i didn’t want to be that person. i have every right to speak up for myself. i am more than just a body. i am strong. ______________

text:
today is the 16 th of december. the day jyoti became the symbol of a woman’s bravery & a victim of the deepest,darkest side of society. #nirbhaya . delhi is slated to celebrate this day with kailash kher’s performance at the mayur utsav. a man who has been accused by multiple women & girls in #metoo ! a serial predator. 
we are asking for more crimes against women in #delhi by calling a serial predator to entertain & headline a govt. show & making him a hero after multiple women have come forward with their traumatic⁠ ⁠stories? does the delhi government care so little about the safety & dignity of #women ? not a single response from the aap government & delhi administration despite my several attempts to reach out to them in the last three days. 
close to 7000 people have signed my petition in the last 36 hours on change.org (link below) & it goes to show that people care & would not want a serial predator like kailash kher to be celebrated by you, #delhi cm arvind kejriwal, culture minister manish sisodia. yet you remain silent? 
dear all, 
please sign & share this link below if you haven’t as yet dear decent people of #india . 
change.org/whykailashkher 🙏🏽🔴

text:
*words._.of._.soul*

i smile today though in pain,
none of your barbs are in vain!
everything matters to me
the hair i cut short, can't you see?
it's not because that i like to be
but for them who love to see my glee
'i don't speak, i don't show
the tears i hide behind that glow.'
for all a damn treat,
'my tears' that man greet!

i remember you touching me through here and there,
i didn't say anything to you,
but you took it as fair.
no it wasn't my crave that i let it do,
what do ya expect a five year old all in woe?
none cared. they all assaulted me as they felt.
but now...
here's a full stop to you and to the eyes pulling towards me.
'cause i'm chaste and you're supppsed to flee.

i am now out of my past.
a big girl so eighteen year old.
i still forgive you everyday-
vow to hew your 'salient' and make you cry to bray.
.
.
.
this is  a saddened voice, trying to fix her gone modest crown, everytime a wolf looks at her the way she was seen in the mid of her hey days! 
praying for such souls.🍁
.
.
.
-manvi j.🖤 @metoomvmt 🌻

text:
thank you to the men who joined voices.
@regran_ed from @morlahdey -  do more for your community!!! on the 15th of december, 2018 we the member of @yalinetworklag in collaboration with @awloint matched out to create and sensitize ikeja community at the early hour of yesterday on the involvement and participation of passionate women in #leadership while we also discuss about our #9javotes2019 campaign awareness activities.

#womendecide is the theme because it's high time passionate women leaders get involved massively in nation development through different platforms that will enhance their leadership skills.

#9javotes2019 by yali lagos is another activities we engage ourselves, so as to learn more about our dear country 2019 forthcoming elections and most importantly on how patriotic citizens should get involved in the electioneering process without violence, selling of vote etc.

while on our way back home, few of us also join #stoprape #stopwomenviolence campaign awareness by some fellow young leaders around shoprite nigeria in ikeja axis to kick against rape and domestic violence that higher percentage of women in our society are always a victim.

let's keep doing more for humanity.

#moreglobal #yalinetwork #awlo - #regrann

text:
сотрудники социальной сети instagram проанализировали поставленные пользователями смайлики, геолокации и хештеги и опубликовали итоги 2018 года. об этом сообщается на официальном сайте instagram.
⠀
таким образом, самой счастливой геолокацией instagram признал диснейленд в токио, так как больше всего счастливых смайликов в 2018 году пользователи ставили именно под фотографиями из японского диснейленда.
⠀
также эксперты назвали самый популярный фильтр для лица: им стал фильтр с сердечками на глазах. а, например, самыми часто используемыми хештегами в 2018 году были #metoo, #timesup и #marchforourlives.
⠀
в ноябре сотрудники британской ассоциации потребителей which составили рейтинг самых безопасных стран для путешествий. специалисты проанализировали 20 самых популярных туристических направлений по четырем критериям: уровень преступности, угроза здоровью, вероятность теракта и стихийных бедствий. самой безопасной страной по всем параметрам стала исландия.

text:
veja o que bombou na retrospectiva do instagram de 2018

#retrospectiva #2018 #retrospectiva2018 #instagram #internet

se você já ficou boiando com algumas hashtags populares no instagram, esse texto é para você. a rede social de fotos divulgou na quinta-feira (13) seus temas mais bombados em 2018, e essa é uma oportunidade para explicarmos todas as tags que você ainda não domina.

as hashtags de movimentos sociais mais compartilhadas do ano foram #metoo (1.5 milhão), #timesup (597 mil) e #marchforourlives (562 mil), o que mostra que o instagram é uma plataforma poderosa para defender suas opiniões e dar visibilidade a causas relevantes. como assim?

o #metoo --"eu também", em inglês-- é uma hashtag originalmente criada para trazer atenção a mulheres vítimas de abusos sexuais. ela surgiu na esteira da série de denúncias contra o produtor de cinema harvey weinstein, que assediou ou estuprou dezenas de mulheres do meio, como gwyneth paltrow e angelina jolie.

os relatos foram organizados no #metoo quando a atriz alyssa milano, em 2017, convocou mulheres que já tinham sido assediadas ou abusadas a responder com um "eu também". no dia seguinte, a hashtag já havia sido utilizada mais de 600 mil vezes.

depois rolou uma resposta chamada #himtoo, criada para trazer atenção a homens vítimas de abusos sexuais, mas que rendeu uma bizarra viralização após o desabafo de uma mãe indignada porque seu filho não arranja namoradas.

já a #timesup também vem do contexto de reação das mulheres ao assédio, pois time's up ("o tempo acabou") é o nome de uma entidade americana fundada por celebridades de hollywood que visa lutar contra o assédio sexual e a discriminação.

#marchforourlives ("marcha por nossas vidas") foi uma demonstração que ocorreu em 24... leia essa matéria na íntegra: http://ow.ly/v8af50jx9xl

text_retweet:
och på hemmaplan läggs jämy ner. skriv under. länk i bio!

#repost @ninarungs with @get_repost
・・・
patriarkatet kämpar för sitt liv. flera tidigare ministrar (bland annat statsminister och utrikesminister) hånar både metoo, en funktionsvarierad kollega och fäller sexistiska kommentarer om kvinnor inom politiken. tar de lite mansvar, ber om ursäkt och avgår? nej. nu kommer svaret: de anmäler kvinnan som avslöjade dom för att hon skadat deras anseende 😳 hon som spelade in deras samtal som vem som helst kunde avlyssna eftersom de satt på en restaurang. en av männen, islands tidigare utrikesminister, har varit en tydlig feministisk röst. och visst är det lite speciellt med män som kommer ut som feminister och samtidigt uttrycker sexism, begår övergrepp på kvinnor eller hatar kvinnor på nätet. ulvarna i fårakläder är ibland svåra att genomskåda. men tack vare #metoo blir fler och fler avklädda. här ser vi patriarkatets sista skälvande yttringar. förklädda till argument om yttrandefrihet och förtal.
name: Carl Adam Tillberg

patriarkatet kämpar för sitt liv. flera tidigare ministrar (bland annat statsminister och utrikesminister) hånar både metoo, en funktionsvarierad kollega och fäller sexistiska kommentarer om kvinnor inom politiken. tar de lite mansvar, ber om ursäkt och avgår? nej. nu kommer svaret: de anmäler kvinnan som avslöjade dom för att hon skadat deras anseende 😳 hon som spelade in deras samtal som vem som helst kunde avlyssna eftersom de satt på en restaurang. en av männen, islands tidigare utrikesminister, har varit en tydlig feministisk röst. och visst är det lite speciellt med män som kommer ut som feminister och samtidigt uttrycker sexism, begår övergrepp på kvinnor eller hatar kvinnor på nätet. ulvarna i fårakläder är ibland svåra att genomskåda. men tack vare #metoo blir fler och fler avklädda. här ser vi patriarkatets sista skälvande yttringar. förklädda till argument om yttrandefrihet och förtal.

text:
instagram подвел итоги 2018 года и назвал самые популярные стикеры, хештеги и сообщества.

самым популярным стикером в «историях» стало сердечко, а самым популярным фильтром — глаза-сердца. эмодзи с сердечком также часто использовали в комментариях — более 14 миллиардов раз.
самым счастливым местом в мире назвали диснейленд в токио, в постах о нем зарегистрировали самое большое количество радостных эмодзи.
главным нишевым трендом года назвали asmr — успокаивающие видео с нарезкой мыла или специальными мягкими игрушками — слаймами. хештег #fortnite стал самым быстрорастущим хештегом в мире.
главным фанатским сообществом на платформе назвали поклонников южнокорейской группы bangtan boys. наиболее вирусным танцем года стал #inmyfeelingschallenge под песню дрейка.
основными хештегами общественных кампаний стали #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597 тысяч), #marchforourlives (562 тысяч)

text:
@regran_ed from @badasscrossstitch -  via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action 
4. contact gov bill haslam’s office and voice your thoughts 1st floor, state capitol nashville, tn 37243 (615) 741-2001 
5. his instagram @governorbillhaslam (remember, he is considering clemency so let’s honor and encourage that) 
6. watch the video: me facing life: cyntoia’s story - google it - it’s on @pbs and you can watch it online. ——————
update:  original art by <<<< @janaillustration >>>follow her! her work is perfection. 
i have tried so hard to find out who made the original piece that i used to stitch this. if you know, please let me know so that i can cite. ——— #blacklivesmatter #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #metoo #justice #freecyntoia #clemencyforcyntoia #resist 
#blm #cyntoiabrown

text: last friday i had the came back for a second serving of the inheritance part 2, one of the theatrical events of the year if you happen to live in london (and especially if you happen to be part of the lgbt+ community). one of the highlights of course is getting to see the legendary vanessa redgrave up close in the play’s only female role, performing a good many times a week at age eighty. i had the chance to see redgrave at the bfi a couple of months ago when she introduced tom jones, directed by her then husband tony richardson. whilst the film remains one of those oscar oddities that has not aged particularly well, it was great to see vanessa reminiscing about that time in the british cinema industry and what it was like to be part of the woodfall troupe of filmmakers (including stories of working methods that would not stand up to scrutiny in the #metoo era). #vanessaredgrave #tomjones #oscars #britishtalent #uk #londonculture #theinheritance #stars #culture #fashion #silverscreen #london #celluloid  #divas #celebrity #celebrities #hollywood #oldhollywood ##influencer #film #filmgeek #filmcritic #ilovefilm #culture #cinephile #cinephilecommunity

text:
i don't know how but i have made it through this week! i am exhausted as my sleep has been shocking, my headaches ongoing and feeling worse by the day, my anxiety has been frustrating and chronic pain issues have had massive swings between good and bad days. not to mention feeling sick and the night terrors linger through the days at time, trying to analyze it or it triggers flashbacks... what can i do?
..
i am putting on a brave face because i don't have a choice really. i can't change what happened last year and how i got to where i am now. life is what it is and i just have to take each day as it comes, be grateful for what i have, even though i feel i could break down and cry at any moment. ..
life is too beautiful and too precious, there is so much to experience and i have way too much to accomplish with my time here ☺, so i keep on going. believe you can and you shall do 🙌🏻💜💜💜 #traumasurvivor #healing #selflove #recovery #strength #support #chronicpain #chronicillness #metoo #cptsdwarrior #anxiety #ptsd #sexualabuse #depression #innerstrength #inspiration #motivation #gratitudeattitude #mentalhealthjourney #lifeisworthit #dontgiveup #youarenotalone #yougotthis #mentalhealthwarrior #youcan #youmatter #life

ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
i am powerfully rooted in the earth, reaching towards the heavens. through the ages i may rise and fall, forever transcending, always connected to the stillness within. 
__________________
the journey has been long; i have lived many lives. discovering my truth, reconciling past karma, honoring my soul. 
__________________
i have learned to forgive those who stole my innocence, defiled my body and bruised my soul. i am a wise warrior who does not fear labels or judgement because i own the strength of my truth. 
__________________
i am here to serve and yet i belong to no one. you are me - i am you - we are one. 
__________________
do not admire my power, as it is also yours. 
__________________
ego climbs the mountain ~ the soul -is- the mountain. release the ego - stand tall as you embrace your soul’s truth and flow into divine stillness.
__________________

text:
selamat ulang tahun teladan!!! seseorang yang akrab kami panggil pak zam yang menurutku guru paling "teladan" di bumi teladan setahun yang lalu. bahkan sempat menjadi kepala sekolah beberapa tahun yang lalu. benar2 guru yang sangat saya kagumi dalam segala hal.

intelektual, emosional, dan spiritual adalah 3 hal yang tidak dapat dipisahkan di teladan. karena e hal tersebutlah teladan tetap menjadi teladan. teladan tidak akan luntur apabila ketiga hal tersebut tertanam baik di bumi teladan.

itulah pesan yang diberikan beliau kepada kami.
terimakasih pak zam.

jangan cari dimana saya. karena saya dibelakang layar 📷

#ph #mpk #2018-2019 #upgrading #spiritofteladan #thebestdayever #teladan #youcandoanything #metoo #teladanday

text:
“mirá como nos ponemos”: cómo se gestó el #metoo argentino

nacida como un conjunto de colegas para luchar por la legalización del aborto, el colectivo de actrices inició el martes una revolución en el medio al acompañar la denuncia de thelma fardin contra darthés “mirá cómo nos ponemos”: el grito de guerra que sonó en el multiteatro porteño el martes ya es hashtag, y se convirtió en primera tendencia global mientras thelma fardín hacía pública su denuncia por violación contra juan darthés. “estamos abriendo una puerta que no se va a cerrar más”, adelantó jazmín stuart, una de las cabezas del colectivo de actrices argentinas que acompañó la denuncia: efectivamente, el martes 11 de diciembre quedará instaurado para siempre como la piedra fundamental del #metoo argentino.

es que algo había que hacer. calu rivero había denunciado mediáticamente a darthés por acoso durante las grabaciones de “dulce amor”, y al galán le dieron el micrófono de mirtha legrand para explicarse. “me acusan de besar mucho”, tiraba en sorna darthés, que además inició acciones legales contra calu, acciones que continúan todavía hoy.

text: many fear their feelings or work hard to avoid the “bad” feelings.  to me, they are feelings - not good; not bad.  when we allow ourselves to feel all of our feelings, we experience life so much more.  being able to feel fear, uncertainty, sadness and anger allows us to enjoy feeling safe, confident, happiness and joy. 💜

جشنواره حرکت در دانشگاه باهنر کرمان، این برد رو دانشجوهای تاریخ درست کردن در ابتدا فقط نقشه ایران بود که بعد گفتن دانشجوها هر کدوم جمله‌ای روش بنویسین که ما هم در حمایت از پویش واژه we exist #lgbt رو نوشتیم که هم اعلام کنیم ما هستیم و از دوستان دیگه دعوت میکنم به کمپین #بیشتر_از_یک_نفر_باشیم بپیوندن، سکوت رو بشکنیم ✌️🏻🌈
.
ما یه کمپین راه انداختیم به اسم #بیشتر_از_یک_نفر_باشیم  منطق این کمپین میخواد سکوت lgbt+های داخل ایران رو بشکنه و باعث میشه دیگران هم به این کمپین بپیوندن، زیر یک دقیقه صحبت میکنید از شرایط از سختی‌ها از مشکلاتی که جامعه ایجاد کرده، به صورت ویدیو نیاز نیست حتما چهرتون مشخص باشه، حرف بزنید و سکوت ال جی بی تی ایران رو بشکنید این حرکت نشون میده شما داخل ایران هستید نه خارج از ایران بین‌ مردم قدم‌ میزنید و وجود دارید.
سکوت نکنید، #ما_همه_جا_هستیم 🏳‍🌈

text:
@keiko_conservation last month, 10 indonesian fishermen working on a japanese longline vessel were caught trying to smuggle 962 #sharkfins in their luggage through honolulu airport. now, five more have been charged, including the two businesses that have ownership of the boat and three of the japanese crew (the captain, fishing master, and first engineer).
according to court documents, all three permitted discarding the shark carcasses and possessing then transporting the fins. the first engineer explicitly directed the indonesian #fishermen to cut off the fins and package some of the fins for himself and the chief officer to take with them after they disembarked. the fishing master, toshiyuki komatsu, ordered the fishermen to not cut the line and release the shark alive as it would mean losing the fishing rigged line and hook. instead he ordered them to kill the sharks or intentionally weaken them to retrieve them. the fishermen admitted that they sometimes cut the line anyways when the fishing master was not looking because they were afraid they would be injured by one of the sharks. the three were not arrested and considered at large, most likely home in japan, but face a maximum fine of $2.75 million each. bringing the fins back to japan would mean they also broke #japanese law by retaining ocean white tip sharks and #silkysharks , both of which are protected species, and by not landing the sharks whole before finning them.
the sharks were most likely fished during their longline tuna #fishing efforts in the southern eastern pacific ocean, ene of #tahiti, approximately a third of the way between tahiti towards mexico. it is estimated 300 #sharks were harvested
more details as well as the court documents can be found on our website (direct page linked in ig story). keikoconservation. say no to #sharkfinsoup #shark second photo illustration credit from @saving.oceans #respectlife #loveanimals #letthembe #theirlivesmatter #lovethemall #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #wildlife #wildlife_perfection #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
estoy leyendo este libro. está excelente. cada vez consigo más evidencia que la reacción de mi familia materna, de querer callar los abusos, es de libro de texto. 
aquí les dejo un pedacito del libro:
“en mi trabajo clínico, he tenido familias que vienen a verme cuando se descubren recientemente las abolladuras del trauma. y a menudo, el que insiste en "mover el bote" es el chivo expiatorio de otros miembros de la familia, dejando a esa persona sintiéndose sola y aislada, como si la insistencia en decir la verdad de alguna manera la vuelve loca ante una expectativa familiar de minimizar el trauma interpersonal, para guardar silencio.”
#seterminaconmigo #yositecreo #abusosexualinfantil #itendswithme #metoo #yotambien #habla #psicologia #trauma #nomassilencio #trabajosocial #socialwork

ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)

ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
#beyourownhero ⤵️ 🐺 
when i was 14 i was manipulated by an “employer” who tried to assault me. when i thought i saw him at school, my safe place, i broke down in the stairwell. one of my classmates found me, and he took me to the guidance counselor who brought in a social worker every week to help me learn to cope. ➖

there are little things, though, like when a man in a passing vehicle cat called me, and i had the audacity to give him an obscene gesture. so he parked and stalked me through the grocery store. i was terrified. ➖

but sometimes, it’s the big things, like when i reached my mid-twenties and suddenly had every adult manifestation of childhood sexual abuse. i can see the flashbacks and relive the pain, but at such a young age, i learned to disassociate from the experience. to this day, i still can’t see the perpetrator’s face. ➖

so call it #metoo or whatever you want, but i’m more than a statistic. i own my demons and they can’t hurt me anymore. ➖

powerlifting might just be a sport to some, but it’s my therapy. it develops my mental fortitude to push through every day and gives me the strength to know that i will never let anyone hurt me like that again. ➖
@davidgoggins 
#badhand #canthurtme #davidgoggins  #challenge #girlswhopowerlift #powerliftingwomen #dirtylaundry

text:
today's inspirator is @justinbaldoni. justin baldoni is an american actor, director, and social entrepreneur. justin who not everyone would say looks like it, has gone through the phase of negative self body image. he talks a lot about this in the manenough episode - "the ugliness of body image" on metoo. in the beginning he states that even though in his movies and shoots he constantly has his shirt off, he still has insecurities about his body. he also feels that what he does, makes other men uncomfortable in their own bodies. just because a man is taking off their shirt, it doesn't always mean they're not insecure. every man has insecurities, but they should never look at other people bodies and aspire to be like that. your body is your body, no one should ever tell you to gain weight, lose weight, get muscles, or grow facial hair to be a "real" man. justin baldoni also makes an appearance on ted talk for why i'm done trying to be "man enough." he goes more in depth about his conflict between how he felt vs what the world was telling he should be as man. society saw him to be this strong man with charisma and power, however he didn't feel that way about himself. he felt like he was pretending to be someone he wasn't. feeling weak and insecure, but pretended to be strong and confident. he acted rough but deep down was hurting, he was just so tired of having to be "man enough" for everyone. why did he have to hide the truth? why did he have to put himself through that, when he could of came out and asked for help. it's not easy. men all around the world are going through the exact same thing, and they can't speak for themselves because it's hard. together we can help them, just like justin baldoni.

text:
ever been told you’re too much?
i have.  a lot. 
too intense
too emotional
too passionate
even too smart. 
so then we try to be smaller, not too much. 
and eventually it comes out in a tidal wave of repression, anger and fear. 
making the right choice everything changes. 
know why?

we feel safe. 
we’re not too much and all the weirdness and kookiness and too muchness can just be. 
we’re not a threat. 
we don’t have to worry about texts not coming fast enough or what’s going on at all times. 
making the right choice means we can be.  and heal.  and grow.  and having all that too muchness we were so afraid of is just loved. 
i wasted a lot of money on love coaches who told me to “get into the vortex” and do mirror work. 
because all those times i tried to shrink the too muchness seemed like just another reason i couldn’t have what i really wanted. 
you know that thing that you think is unloveable?  yeah that.  no amount of mirror work alone or vortex meditations are going to heal that.  trust me i tried. 
goddess, you deserve to feel safe.  and kooky and free. 
in the arms of the wrong man you will be too much. 
in the arms of the right man you are 10 times the woman you have been. 
i was the poster child for choosing assholes. if i can leave them behind, anyone can. 
let’s have this be the year you heal. 
we got this. ❤️💕💗

text:
no one ever asks what made you gain weight.
.
i never thought i’d be brave enough to share this part of my life.
.
though this is painful to share, i know we are stronger when we talk about our struggles-and i hope you will share yours with me below. (#metoo)
.
when i was 21 i was slipped a date-rape drug. 
the remaining details are not significant to my story, but something was taken from me that night that i’ll never get back.
.
the final words i was left with were “i only gave you what you deserved”...which were words that pierced my heart and mind for many years to come.
.
what i...deserved???
.
i immediately turned to food for comfort. honestly, the more weight i gained-the safer i felt. i felt like if i was overweight, no one would find me attractive and i wouldn’t ever get hurt again.
.
but the weight that i carried pierced much deeper.
.
instead of dealing with it, i tucked it away in my mind and hoped i would never have to face it. i started eating my feelings instead...
.
the sad reality is: 1 in 6 women will be a victim of sexual assault/rape. and it’s something we don’t talk about. at least i didn’t for many years. it was a secret i hid from the world because i felt so ashamed.
.
nobody is deserving of that. nobody. and it took me many years to fully believe that.
.
i didn’t take care of myself anymore...
i didn’t love myself anymore...
food was the only comfort that i had...
the thought of taking it away made me uncomforable.
.
but i took my life back...and so can you.
.
i share this with you, because i know i’m not alone. many of us had an event that triggered us to gain weight. but the beautiful thing is: you have the power within you to overcome it.
.
we are not defined by our past. 
we are not what had happened to us. 
we have the power to design a bright future and never look back. 
we have nothing to be ashamed of.
.
our trials can become our triumphs.
our tests can become our testimony. 
our messes can become our message.
.
and i know that if i can overcome my struggles...so can you.
.
📷 @weightlosshero
.
follow @whyweighttv for more!
.
www.whyweight.tv

no one ever asks what made you gain weight.
.
i never thought i’d be brave enough to share this pa of my life.
.
though this is painful to share, i know we are stronger when we talk about our struggles-and i hope you will share yours with me below. (etoo)
.
when i was 21 i was slipped a date-rape drug. 
the remaining details are not significan not to my story, but something was taken from me that night that i’ll never get back.
.
the final words i was left with were “i only gave you what you deserved”...which were words that pierced my hea and mind for many years to come.
.
what i...deserved???
.
i immediately turned to food for comfo. honestly, the more weight i gained-the safer i felt. i felt like if i was overweight, no one would find me attractive and i wouldn’t ever get hu again.
.
but the weight that i carried pierced much deeper.
.
instead of dealing with it, i tucked it away in my mind and hoped i would never have to face it. i staed eating my feelings instead...
.
the sad reality is: 1 in 6 women will be a victim of sexual assault/rape. and it’s something we don’t talk about. at least i didn’t for many years. it was a secret i hid from the world because i felt so ashamed.
.
nobody is deserving of that. nobody. and it took me many years to fully believe that.
.
i didn’t take care of myself anymore...
i didn’t love myself anymore...
food was the only comfo that i had...
the thought of taking it away made me uncomforable.
.
but i took my life back...and so can you.
.
i share this with you, because i know i’m not alone. many of us had an event that triggered us to gain weight. but the beautiful thing is: you have the power within you to overcome it.
.
we are not defined by our past. 
we are not what had happened to us. 
we have the power to design a bright future and never look back. 
we have nothing to be ashamed of.
.
our trials can become our triumphs.
our tests can become our testimony. 
our messes can become our message.
.
and i know that if i can overcome my struggles...so can you.
.

text:
some people come in our lives to love us,

some come in our lives to rob us of our dignity, pride and prized possessions

some come in our lives with lessons to change our life

but once in a while comes a special someone who makes you feel a little different, a little loved and most of all make us see the goodness in us.

with his eyes i saw goodness in me, which i once thought was robbed, looted and exploited. before he came i was something else, something close to a pessimist. someone who was ready to throw herself off the cliff, but fate had something else. he never demanded a change. he loved all formes of me- even the sad, broken and devastated version of me. my broken heart used to hurt a lot, which i never thought could be reversed. but his love was like magic. he made me feel beautiful again, made me believe that i was worthy of being loved again. and most of all, made me believe that i could love again.

he made me believe that i wasn’t any empty vessel, i still had endless love to offer. he changed me, without even asking me to change. he came in my life when i was at my lowest, and with him, i have only risen higher.

with him, i find it easier to battle my negatively,

with him, i realized i was never a salve to this society, but i was trapped in the cage built inside my mind. he liberated me of all burdens.

with him, i find in myself a little more strength to combat depression,

with him, i believe in myself a little more,

with him, i fear a little less and love a little more…
.
- a tribute to raju jana @iam_awsm
.
(- from khushboo rani mahato @this_chick_writes)
.
--------×--------
.
in these times of #metoo and stories of sexual harassment, there are also women and men around us who made us feel more beautiful, more confident and powerful from both inside and out. 
if there is a person who brought some meaningful changes in your life, then let's pay a tribute to her/him right here at @shespeaksforthechange.

we all need such people around us afterall, don't we?
